title: blackberry vinaigrette
directions: Place cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Gradually add water, whisking until blended.
Stir in blackberry vinegar and remaining ingredients.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool to room temperature, then refrigerate.
Serve over a combination of gourmet mixed lettuce, thinly sliced red onion and chopped fresh mint.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil.
Mix flour, sugar and soda together.
Mix with hot mixture. Stir in sour milk.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a 12 x 15-inch greased and floured pan for 20 minutes at 325°.
Frost.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Season to taste with Tony's Creole seasoning.
Debone chicken.
Use broth from chicken and 2 cans chicken broth.
Combine flour, egg and milk; mix well.
Roll out on floured surface, using rolling pin.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mix ingredients in order and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use straw test.

title: easy baklava
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 8 sheets of filo, buttering each sheet.
Sprinkle some nuts over filo, then build up layers of a single sheet of filo (buttered), sprinkle with nuts, etc., reserving 8 sheets for the top layers.
Score with a very sharp knife in diamond pattern (or squares).
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until nicely browned.
Remove from oven; immediately pour honey over Baklava.
When cool, store in airtight container. This keeps for a very long time.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Run cold water over vegetables to separate.
In a large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is brown; drain.
Stir vegetables and 1/4 cup water into skillet.
Cook, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir in soup, Worcestershire sauce, thyme and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.
Transfer to a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Prepare potatoes according to package directions.
Drop in mound atop hot mixture.
If desired, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Serves 4.

title: calamai con pomodoro(squid with tomatoes)
directions: Clean squid.
Cut into small pieces.
Pour oil into saucepan and heat.
Brown garlic for 3 minutes.
Add squid.
Cover and saute for 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and basil.
Lower heat and cook 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and parsley, cover and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Serve very hot on heated dishes.
Serves 8.

title: tropical fruit smoothie
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Sift flour together.
Add alternating with milk.
Stir in vanilla. Pour into three 9-inch pans and bake at 350° until brown.

title: pineapple lime basic salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple and chill until thickened.
Add sour cream and pour into a 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Chill until set.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together thoroughly.
Add the eggs, syrup, salt, and vanilla extract.
Beat well.
Pour into 9-inch pastry shell.
Scatter pecans over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until firm.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese; mix in remaining ingredients.
Form into ball.
Pat with chopped pecans.
Store in refrigerator.
May be frozen.

title: pretzel salad(kids love it.)
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes and put in freezer for a while.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Grease & flour bundt pan. Preheat over to 325°. Combine butter and sugar. Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs - one at a time. Beat well. Add flour, beat in extract and 7-up. Pour into pan. Bake for 1 1/4 hours.

title: white chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix together first five ingredients and then melt 1/2 box of the white baking chocolate in the microwave and add to the cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. While the cake is still hot, melt 1-2 c. of chocolate chips in the microwave with 2-3 Tbsp. butter until slightly thin and spreadable. (You may need to add a bit more butter.) Spread this on top of the cake while it is still hot. Place in the refrigerator overnight. The next day, mix 1 can vanilla frosting, 1 tsp. vanilla and the other half of white chocolate (melted). Mix together well then add Cool Whip. Spread on cooled cake. Keep refrigerated.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice.
Combine pineapple, mandarin orange sections, maraschino cherries, bananas and pecans in a large bowl; toss gently.

title: low-fat berry bavarian
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl 2 minutes or completely dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice cubes to make 2 cups.
Add to gelatin; stir until slightly thickened.
Remove remaining ice cubes.

title: michelle's macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on box. Mix all other ingredients and add to macaroni and cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: sprite scratch pineapple coconut cake
directions: Pour cooking oil, 3 whole eggs, 2 egg whites, sugar and pudding mix and mix.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture with Sprite soda and mix.
Add vanilla and lemon flavor. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: round steak
directions: Cut steak in pieces.
Dip in flour; fry in oil until brown. Put the onion soup mix, flour and water and mix together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add meat.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: frozen mashed potato casserole
directions: Put first three ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil. Stir in instant potatoes.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix with mixer.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Fill with potato mixture.
Freeze if you want to use later, or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on and continue baking until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: raisin peanut drops
directions: Cover a large cookie sheet with wax paper or aluminum foil; set aside.
Place broken candy bars in a 2-quart measure or casserole. Microwave on High 1 minute; stir.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes or just until most chocolate pieces melt.
Stir until all chocolate melts and its smooth.
Stir in raisins, peanuts and marshmallows. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto covered cookie sheet.
Let cool until firm.
Store in an airtight container.

title: el paso burgers
directions: Chop onion and green pepper finely.
Add onion, pepper, taco seasoning to meat.
Mix well.
Divide meat into 8 equal balls and form patties.
Grill to desire doneness.
Top with a slice of cheese and salsa.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 8 burgers.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve soft drink mix in milk; fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours or until set.

title: berry salad
directions: Combine berries in a large bowl.
Add yogurt and almond extract, mixing gently with the berries.
Garnish with mint leaves.
Chill until serving time.
Great for brunch or anytime. Serves 8.

title: cheese balls with ripe olives
directions: Cream, let chill, divide into 2 balls and roll in chopped nuts.

title: fruit cocktail cake b.j.s.
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add eggs and undrained fruit cocktail; blend well.
Pour into 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back.
Remove from oven, but let stand in pan or rack while preparing topping.

title: ritz cracker slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
After all is mixed, sprinkle cheese over top.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving. Great for company.

title: beef-barley-kale soup
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil.
In a large pot, combine broth and barley and cook for 1 hour along with beef and onions.
In last 5 minutes, add the kale and mushrooms.
On one occasion, I added a tablespoon sesame oil and that was interesting.
I usually try to use fresh kale, stem and all.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and 3/4 cup of peanut butter with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Spread with the other half of peanut butter.
Top with Cool Whip as desired and refrigerate.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.
Place flour in a large bowl and add dates, chopped candy and nuts.
Stir to coat.
Add flour and fruit mixture and coconut to creamed mixture.
This makes a very stiff dough that should be mixed with hands.
Put in a greased 13 x 9 x 3-inch cake pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Combine orange juice and powdered sugar.
Pour over hot cake.
Let stand in pan overnight.

title: orange-cranberry refresher(punch)
directions: Combine
juices and wine.
chill.
Just before serving, add carbonated water.
Pour into pitcher.
Garnish with orange slices. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: crispy oven fried mexican chicken
directions: Combine V-8 and hot sauce.
Add chicken parts and marinate for 30 minutes at room temperature.
Drain chicken and discard marinade.
In a large plastic bag, combine remaining ingredients. Coat each piece of chicken and place in a baking pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over chicken. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.
Equals:
3 proteins, 1/2 ounce hard cheese, 1/2 bread.

title: best ever banana pudding
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together until pudding is smooth. Fold in whipped cream.
Layer pudding with bananas and vanilla wafers in a large serving bowl.
Serves 10.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8-inch layers.
When completely cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, blending well.
Chill.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread the remainder between layers of cake.
Combine the reserved sour cream mixture with whipped topping.
Blend well until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal cake in an airtight container and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onions in drippings.
Mix beans and all remaining ingredients with sauteed bacon and onions.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: crab meat bisque
directions: Mix undiluted soups.
Bring to a boil.
Add cream, sherry, crab meat and salt.
Make early in the day; let stand.
Reheat before serving.
Add extra sherry, if desired.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and pour into baking dish.

title: fudge squares
directions: Melt the chocolate over hot water or in microwave.
Mix shortening and sugar, add eggs unbeaten.
Add the chocolate and stir.
Add the flour, baking powder, and salt alternately with the milk.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending well into the mixture.
Fold topping into peanut butter mixture.
Pour into pie crust. Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Chill until firm.

title: mama's mini-cinnis
directions: Unroll crescent rolls. Separate each dough portion along center perforations to form 4 triangles. Press diagonal perforation to seal. Stir together butter and the next 4 ingredients. Spread mixture over one side of each triangle. Roll up jelly roll fashion, starting at long end. Gently cut each log into 6 (1-inch thick) slices.

Place roll 1/4-inch apart on 2 (8-inch) cake pans. Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes, until lightly browned. Cool 5 to 10 minutes. Stir together powdered sugar and remaining ingredients. Drizzle over warm rolls.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Bake in crust at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg and molasses and beat until well blended.
Sift flour.
Measure and add salt, soda and spices.
Sift again.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Chill dough in refrigerator.
Shape the chilled dough into balls 1-inch in diameter.
Roll balls in granulated sugar and place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate fluff
directions: Mix
flour,
butter and pecans together, press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.	Chill.

title: hot mix
directions: In sterilized quart jar, place the first four ingredients. Prepare vegetables and add to jar in layers.
Combine vinegar and water in small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables in jar.
Cover jar with lid; cool.
Chill in refrigerator.
This keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots with sugar and salt until almost done.
Drain. Soften Velveeta in microwave.
Add butter, onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix cheese mixture and carrots.
Pour in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with cornflakes or Ritz crackers, crushed.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar but do not boil.
Mix all vegetables together.
Be sure the sugar is dissolved.
Pour it over vegetables.
Place in a tightly covered container in fridge.
Stir often.
Keeps well in fridge.

title: applesauce-raisin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Mix all ingredients thoroughly; spread in pan.
Bake 25 minutes. Frost with Buttercream Frosting.
Cut into bars (about 3 x 1-inch).
Makes 32.

title: easy toffee candy
directions: Place saltine crackers side-by-side on bottom of a jelly roll pan.
Boil 1/3 cup butter and 1 cup brown sugar for 3 minutes. Pour boiled mixture over crackers.
Bake at 375° for 4 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate bar pieces (spread evenly).
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts.
Let cool.
Break into appropriate size pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Chop in small pieces. Cook noodles in chicken broth until tender.
Add salt, pepper and butter to taste.
Mix chicken and noodles together and put in casserole dish.
Pour cream of chicken soup over this mixture and put in oven 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.
Just long enough for all ingredients to mix well.

title: classic pesto sauce
directions: Be sure basil contains only leaves, no stems!
Place basil, garlic and pine nuts in food processor until nearly smooth.
Add oil and cheese; process again.
(If making for freezer, omit cheese and add it when ready to use.)
Makes about 1 cup or enough to dress 1 1/2 pounds of pasta.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken.
Add all seasonings.
After done, debone chicken and then add 1 can of broth and bouillon cubes.
(Cut up fine the celery stalks, carrots and onion.)
Cook until done.
Add noodles. Lastly add meat.
Great with cornbread.

title: little league casserole
directions: You will place in layers.
Cover greased casserole with onion rings, layer of potatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Spread beef, beans and pour on canned tomatoes. Cut bacon and place on top. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
The last 15 minutes, place cheese triangles on top.
Finish baking 15 more minutes.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in casserole, set in shallow pan of water, 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken with curry-peach sauce
directions: About 30 minutes before serving:
In nonstick 12 inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 1 Tbsp. hot salad oil, cook chicken and salt until chicken is browned on both sides.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook until chicken is tender and juices run clear when pieces are pierced with tip of knife.
Remove chicken to plate; keep warm.

title: green chile 'n cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place one biscuit in the center of cookie sheet, arrange remaining biscuits in circle, edges slightly overlapping, around center biscuit.
Gently press out to 10-inch circle.
In small bowl combine margarine and chili powder; brush over biscuits.
Sprinkle with chilies and cheese.
Bake in oven for 10 to 17 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Pull apart and enjoy!!

title: black walnut chess
directions: Beat butter and sugar in bowl. Add flour, salt, egg yolks and milk; beat with mixer until well mixed. Stir in vanilla and walnuts. Pour mixture into chilled pie shell. Bake on lower shelf of 375° oven for 45 minutes, until center is almost set but still soft. Cool thoroughly on wire rack.

title: red salad dressing
directions: Put the amount of ingredients you want and mix well.
Good on head of lettuce or other mixed salads.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam.
Layer chopped chicken. Mix soup and broth and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drain Veg-All and peas and put on top of the soup layer. Melt margarine and pour over vegetables.
Mix Bisquick and milk and pour on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until golden and bubbly (about 45 to 55 minutes).

title: best-ever muffins
directions: Mix together flour with sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine egg and milk and add all at once to flour mixture.
Add shortening.
Then stir only until dry ingredients are moistened. (Batter will be lumpy.)
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling each about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done. Makes 10 muffins.

title: microwave coconut pie
directions: Put in microwave-safe large bowl and cook 6 minutes.
Stir. Cook another 4 minutes.
Add margarine, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into prebaked crust or graham cracker crust and store in refrigerator.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet until browned.
Add hash browns and cook until tender.
While cooking, beat together eggs and milk.
Add to sausage/hash brown mixture.
Cook until eggs are set (almost done).
Put in 4 ounces of cheese and cook until melted. Pour mixture into a sprayed 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Serve with picante sauce (if desired).

title: banana cookies
directions: Mix and let set.
Drop on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix together well and put into ice cream freezer.
Follow manufacturer's directions on your freezer for freezing ice cream.

title: church potatoes
directions: Combine
all but the last 2 ingredients in a casserole. Mix cracker crumbs with 1/4 cup melted butter and spread this mixture over
the
top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: squash balls
directions: Mix
first
ingredients.
Add enough crushed cracker crumbs until
mixture becomes stiff.
Make out into balls and roll in more cracker crumbs and fry slow until golden brown.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until fine grain.
Add 1/2 cup cold milk; mix.
Roll out on floured board.
Makes 3 single crusts.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Combine eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Pour all at once into well.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix.
Gently fold in jam (a few lumps will remain).
Place in greased or paper lined muffin tins.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Yields 18 muffins.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: While searing spareribs in oven, fry onion in saucepan.
After onion is brown, add other ingredients and let simmer until spareribs are ready.
Pour over ribs and bake in oven at 325° until ribs are done.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour and beat thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to blend well. Turn batter into a greased and floured pan, 11 x 7 x 2-inch or 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: green chile enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas until crisp and layer in 2-quart casserole with cheese and onions.
Mix together soup, milk and green chiles and pour over top.
Top with remaining grated cheese and bake in oven 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: 7-up applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot applesauce; add 7-Up, blending gently. Chill until set.
Nuts and celery are optional and may be added when gelatin is slightly thickened.

title: squash supreme
directions: Mash squash; add sour cream, soup, carrot, onion, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle a layer of crumbs in casserole dish.
Spoon squash mixture over crumbs and dot generously with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: summer asparagus salad
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add celery and asparagus. Wait 5 minutes.
Quickly put celery and asparagus in ice bath, then add remaining ingredients and serve.

title: banana fruit slush
directions: Stir together the water and sugar until the sugar is dissolved.
Add juices and bananas and mix well.
Pour into 2 1/2-gallon freezer containers or clean milk cartons.
Cover and freeze at least 24 hours or up to 6 months.
To serve, let thaw at room temperature about 4 hours until mixture is slushy, then add Sprite.
If thawing half of recipe, add only 2 cups Sprite.

title: shrimp-crab dish
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is crisp.

title: baked ziti with sausage
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving:
In saucepot, prepare ziti as label directs, but do not use salt in water.
Drain ziti and return to pan.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Combine beef and onions.
Cook until done and drain.
In a large pot combine beef mixture and remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes and then simmer on low for 1 hour.

title: waikiki meat balls
directions: Mix
thoroughly
the
beef,
crumbs,
onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls. Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown and cook meat balls. Remove
meat balls; keep warm.
Pour fat from skillet. Mix cornstarch	and sugar.
Stir in reserved pineapple syrup, vinegar and
soy sauce until smooth.
Pour into skillet.
Cook over medium
heat
until mixture thickens and boils, stirring constantly.
Boil
and stir 1 minute.
Add meat balls, pineapple and green pepper.
Heat through.

title: golden carrots supreme
directions: Add butter to boiling chicken broth.
Stir in salt, pepper, sugar and carrots.
Simmer, covered, until carrots are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and parsley. Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen mint salad
directions: Mix pineapple with juice, lime jello and marshmallows and let stand overnight.
Next morning, crush mints fine and add to jello mixture.
Whip in the whipping cream and fold into mixture.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or place in jello mold.
Freeze.
Keep in freezer when not serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a double boiler, cook sugar, cornstarch, boiling water and salt until thick.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O and cool.
Add 1 quart strawberries.
Pour into two 8-inch pie shells.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook and drain hamburger meat. Mix all ingredients and heat. Eat over rice or Fritos.

title: new england baked beans(crock-pot)
directions: Cook dry beans in water until softened.
(Simmer in 3 times their volume of unsalted water for 30 minutes in a saucepan. Allow to stand, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until softened; drain and add remaining ingredients.)
Mix well.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours (high for 4 to 6 hours), stirring occasionally.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake as directed; cool completely.
Make Jell-O and chill.
Put pineapple and cherries on bottom of cake pan.
Put Jell-O on top of pineapple and cherries.
Put whipped cream on top of Jell-O, put cake on top of whipped cream, then pour rest of Jell-O all around sides of cake.
Let stand in refrigerator for about 4 hours.
Set in hot water for a few seconds.
Turn upside down on plate.
Cake will fall out.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice dough off into 1/4-inch thick pieces.
Press out evenly on pizza pan.
Bake dough as package directs, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar with cream cheese and spread over cookie dough.
Drain fruit well, even lay out on paper towels. Save 1 cup of the juices to be used later.
Slice fruit evenly on top.

title: louise's herb toast
directions: Take crusts off bread.
Mix herbs in softened butter.
Spread mixture thinly on bread (enough mixture for 18 slices at least). Cut each slice of bread into 3 strips.
Bake strips on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden toasted.
Cool and keep in airtight container.
Delicious with a drink!

title: olive spread
directions: Mash softened cream cheese with a fork.
Then add mayonnaise and blend well.
Stir in pecans and olives.
(Notice the recipe calls for salad olives; since they are chopped up anyway, don't spend extra money for the more expensive whole ones.)
Add olive juice and dash of pepper, but no salt.
Stir well.
This mixture will be slightly mushy.
Refrigerate for several hours in a covered container and it will become firm.

title: polish lasagna
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Put some onion-margarine mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese with hands until smooth.
Work in dry ingredients until a firm dough is made.
Roll into straws.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: fruit cake squares
directions: Grease 10 x 15 pan. Dust lightly with flour. Spread 2 cups nuts on bottom of pan. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add flour, salt and flavoring. Spoon over nuts. Wet hands and pat gently to smooth out butter. Mix all fruit together. Spoon fruit mixture over batter. Again, pat fruit into batter using wet hands. Bake 1 hour at 290°. Cut while hot. Let cool.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, lemon juice, vanilla extract and condensed sweetener in mixing bowl.
Use blender until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Pour mixture into pie pan and refrigerate until firm (about 2 hours).
Smooth fruit atop pie and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve chilled.

title: light dilled potato salad
directions: In large bowl sprinkle oil and vinegar over potatoes.
Toss lightly to coat.
Combine mayonnaise, yogurt and mustard.
Add this mixture and remaining ingredients to potatoes.
Toss to coat. Cover and chill.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: macaroni and cheese plus
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
When drained, return to cooking pot.
Add cheese sauce and stir the tomato sauce, mushrooms and olives in.
Heat thoroughly and serve hot. Add a tossed salad and dessert for a quick and easy meal.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hidden valley ranch round-ups
directions: Combine salad dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Spread thin layer of salad dressing on bread.
Top each piece with a few shreds of cheese and thinly sliced vegetables.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until crispy.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Sprinkle cubed bread on bottom of greased 9 x 11-inch pan. Sprinkle cooked sausage on top of bread.
Add cheese.
Combine eggs, salt, mustard and half and half.
Mix with whisk beater. Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, uncover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add well-beaten eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add flour and milk alternately, then add vanilla.
Pour into 3 greased pans and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Season hamburger.
Add 1 can of cream soup and milk.
Heat and serve over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: bobalky
directions: Place butter, margarine, sugar and salt in mixing bowl and add scalded milk; let cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast dissolved in water.
Add enough flour to to make a soft elastic dough.
Turn onto a floured board and knead.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour, in a warm place.
Punch dough down with fingertips and let rise again about another hour. Toss lightly on floured board; knead and shape into a roll, about 1/2-inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cut with edge of teaspoon into small pieces and let rise 10 minutes.

title: baked chicken in foil
directions: Place chicken, potatoes, carrots and onions in foil; season. Pour melted oleo over all.
Close foil tightly.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Also can be placed in crock-pot on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and pimento in a 1/2 stick of butter.
Combine cooked rice, eggs, corn and salt and pepper to taste with the sauteed mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp linguine
directions: Cook linguine al dente; drain.
Cook shrimp in boiling water until pink; drain and cool.
Carefully remove shell from each shrimp, leaving the tail intact.
Devein shrimp.
(You should have about 2 cups cooked shrimp.)
In a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine mushrooms, margarine, green onions and garlic. Micro-cook, covered, on 100% power (High), 2 to 3 minutes or until onions are tender.
Stir in the shrimp, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley, wine, basil and pepper.
Micro-cook, uncovered, on High for 30 seconds or until heated through.
Add linguine to shrimp mix.
Toss to mix.
Serve immediately.
Put additional cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: oriental beef
directions: Sprinkle meat tenderizer over meat in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add all ingredients except pea pods and mix well to coat evenly. Cover with casserole lid.
Microwave (High) 13 to 14 minutes or until meat is just about tender, stirring twice.
Add pea pods; cover.
Microwave (High) 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once.
Serve over rice.

title: 1 small pan brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, flour and cocoa; fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mark's jello
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water until dissolved.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
In 9 x 13-inch glass dish, place sliced bananas. Cover bananas with 1/2 of Jell-O mixture.
Let chill until firm. Spread sour cream on top of Jell-O.
Pour remaining Jell-O mixture on top of sour cream and chill until set.

title: southern sweet potato salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook sweet potatoes in boiling, salted water just until tender, about 5 to 8 minutes (do not overcook). Drain; toss with the lemon juice.
In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, orange juice, honey, orange peel, ginger, salt and nutmeg.
Add the warm potatoes, celery and dates.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Before serving, gently stir in the pecans.
Spoon salad onto a lettuce-lined platter.
Arrange oranges around salad.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown meat.
Cook onion in butter until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes.
Stir now and then.
Serve over hot, cooked noodles.

title: spaghetti
directions: Put all in a pan and simmer slowly for 4 hours.
Stir frequently.
Let cool, then skim grease off top.
Reheat for dinner.

title: delicious lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, adding the oil and bay leaves to the boiling water.
Oil an 12 x 18-inch baking dish, starting with noodles.
Make layers of noodles and 1/3 of the savory meat sauce, along with 1/2 of the cottage cheese. Sprinkle the Parmesan.
Add a few slices of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas style baked beans
directions: Boil the beans, bacon, onions and salt and pepper together for 2 to 5 minutes.
Allow to sit for 1 hour, then continue cooking until beans are tender.
Drain.
In a large baking pan, mix the strained beans, and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours to desired thickness.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender; debone and chop into bite size pieces.
Put all ingredients in large pot on top of stove and simmer 30 minutes.
Makes 4 cups.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: saag aloo - spinach and potato stew (india)
directions: Put spinach and potatoes in large pot; cover with warm water and bring to boil.
Simmer about 12 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Saute onion and garlic; add all spices except salt and saute a minute more.
Remove from heat.
Drain potato mixture; reheat onion and spice mixture.
Add potato mixture and gently stir to blend.
Taste and add salt as desired.
Simmer over low heat another 10 minutes until mixture is fairly dry and spices have been absorbed by vegetables.

title: spiced apricots
directions: Wash apricots.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Add sugar, water and spices.
Cover.
Microwave 20 to 25 minutes on High or until fruit is tender and flavors have blended.

title: yummy chocolate fudge cake
directions: While cake is still warm, take a wooden spoon and poke holes all over with the handle.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the cake. Spread fudge topping over cake.
Whip the whipping cream and frost cake (or use Cool Whip).
Top with crushed Heath bars.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pie filling and wafers) until smooth.
Line cupcake tins with cupcake papers.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in each cupcake paper.
Fill 3/4 full with cheese mixture. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Top with pie filling.

title: chicken and rice with creamy herb sauce
directions: Bring 3/4 cup hot water, Chablis and bouillon granules to a boil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and add chicken; cover and simmer 15 minutes, turning chicken after 8 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet; set aside and keep warm. Bring cooking liquid to a boil; cook 5 minutes or until reduced to 2/3 cup.
Combine cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water.
Stir well and add to skillet.
Bring to a boil; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and cook until well blended, stirring constantly with a wire whisk.
To serve, top rice with chicken. Spoon sauce over chicken.
Garnish with parsley.

title: layered toffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream just until it begins to thicken. Gradually add the ice cream topping and vanilla, beating until soft peaks form. Cut cake horizontally into three layers. Place the bottom layer on serving plate; spread with 1 cup cream mixture and sprinkle with 1/2 cup toffee bits. Repeat. Place top layer on cake; frost top and sides with remaining cream mixture and sprinkle with remaining toffee bits. Store in refrigerator. Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: clam linguine
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions, omitting the salt.
Drain and set it aside.
Saute garlic in butter in a large skillet.
Drain clams; add juice to skillet and bring to a boil. Cook over medium heat.
Add clams and cheese; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Pour sauce over linguine and add parsley.
Toss gently.

title: decadent fudge frosting
directions: Combine chopped white chocolate and 2 tablespoons shortening in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until mixture is melted and smooth.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Drizzle melted white chocolate mixture over cooled cake. Melt semi-sweet chocolate mini morsels and 2 teaspoons shortening in a small saucepan.
Remove from heat and let cool; drizzle over white chocolate.

title: meatballs
directions: Soak bread in water and squeeze out moisture.
Mix all ingredients; shape mixture into balls and cook.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Combine all other ingredients and spread in a 9 by 13 inch baking dish.
Lay chops on top and season with salt and pepper.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: no crust sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in skillet or baking dish. Bake at 325° until firm.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, dump pineapple and dump in cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over all.
Sprinkle on nuts and sliced oleo.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy apricot strudel
directions: Combine
flour,
sour
cream and butter in mixing bowl. Blend well, cover;
chill
at
least 1 hour.
Roll out chilled dough, one fourth at a time to a 13 x 6-inch rectangle on well floured surface.
Spread
cup preserves along one 13-inch side to the width
of
1/2-inches.
Sprinkle
with 1/4 cup coconut and
2 tablespoons nuts.
Starting with 13-inch side, roll up jelly
roll fashion.
Seal edges and ends.
Place seam side down on
ungreased cookie
sheet.
Use
same
method for remaining fourths of chilled dough.
Bake at 450° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool, sprinkle
with
powdered
sugar.
Cut
into slices.
Makes about 48
slices. Can be frozen before baking. Remove from freezer, defrost and bake as directed.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook the squash with onion; drain.
Mix flour, milk and cheese and pour over squash.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: candy coated popcorn
directions: Place syrup, sugar, margarine, salt and water in two-quart pot.
Cook over low to medium heat to 300° (hard crack stage). Stir in nuts, add baking soda in hot water to hot syrup and stir well.
Pour hot syrup and nuts over popped corn in large greased pan.
Mix syrup and corn rapidly.
Spread thinly on cookie sheets or wax paper and let cool.
Store in closed container.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, put into 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until heated thoroughly.

title: broccoli-cheese-onion casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	according to package instructions.
Put in casserole
dish.
Cover with cheese, onion soup mix and 3/4 of the onion rings.
Combine in a separate bowl the soup, milk and water. Pour
this
liquid over broccoli mixture.	Cook at 350°, covered,
for 25 minutes.
Remove cover.
Add remaining onion rings
to
cooked
mixture.
Bake
an
additional 3 to 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Combine cream cheese, flour and butter; squash with fingers until mixed.
Roll out on a floured board; press rounds into little tart or muffin tins.
Mix together pecans, brown sugar, egg, melted butter, vanilla and salt.
Spoon into crusts, filling half full. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until nicely browned.
Makes 12 to 24 tarts, depending on size of tins.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Mix in order given.
Bake 1 hour in loaf pan at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt fat, brown hamburg and then add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Put in greased dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 2 hours.

title: my moms baked beans
directions: Dice bacon and brown with onion.
Add tomatoes and cook until soft.
Add brown sugar and catsup.
Mix well.
Add beans.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
In shallow baking pan, shape into loaf. Bake 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: farmer's breakfast
directions: In large pan, cook onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add Spam, potatoes and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add eggs, water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper; pour over Spam mixture.
Cook over low heat until set.
Can be used as a breakfast, a dinner or for supper.

title: broiled barbecued beef
directions: Place flank steak in glass baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over steak.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours, turning once.
Place steak on broiler rack. Brush with marinade. Broil 3-inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn and brush with marinade.
Broil 3 minutes or until desired doneness.

title: gladys' barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over meat or chicken in pan.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Quarter cucumbers and place in gallon wide mouth jar; add salt, then cover with boiling water.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse well.
Heat vinegar, pickling spice, celery and mustard seed, turmeric, alum and 1 cup of sugar.
When heated, pour over cucumbers.
Next A.M., add 1 cup of sugar and mix in jar.
Do this for a total of 4 days.
There will be 5 cups of sugar in all.
Do not heat after first day.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all the above and put in pan for baking.
Cover with decorative slices of bacon.
Cook at 350° in oven for 1 1/2 hours. Serve hot.

title: cranberry apple cake
directions: In a mixing bowl cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add applesauce; blend well.
Thoroughly stir together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Stir in oats and cranberry sauce.
Spread into a floured and greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and place on a rack.
Wrap and store at least 1 to 2 days.
Serve warm or cool with Cool Whip.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a deep pie shell (unbaked).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corn-green bean casserole
directions: Drain corn and beans and mix.
Put in 8 x 8 x 3-inch baking dish.
Mix sour cream, soup, onion and cheese.
Spread over vegetables.
Mix crackers, oleo and almonds; spread on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Warm milk.
Add marshmllows and nuts; stirring until dissolved.
Pour over mixture of other ingredients and mix.
Pack into a waxed paper lined pan.
Refrigerate.
Makes 8 to 10 pounds.

title: cheese roll
directions: Combine all cheeses and sauces.
Make into a ball and roll in chili powder and paprika mixture.

title: orange bran muffins
directions: Combine raisins, apples and orange juice; let soak 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 2 (8 cup) muffin pans with paper liners.
In large bowl, sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Add cereal and mix thoroughly.
In another bowl, beat egg, milk and oil.
Make well in center of dry ingredients and pour egg mixture in.
Add raisin mixture and stir. Do not overbeat.
Fill cups 3/4 full and bake 18 to 20 minutes. Test with toothpick.
Transfer muffins to rack to cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, eggs and milk in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; mix well and pour into baked pie shell. Refrigerate.

title: french red dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat on high with mixer for 15 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add Wesson oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add pineapple and juice from pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Mix well and pour into 3 cake pans that are sprayed well with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely before icing.

title: progresso chicken casserole
directions: Coat chicken cubes with eggs and Italian crumbs.
Brown in margarine.
Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Pour mushrooms and liquid over top.
Grate Muenster cheese over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ghostly grub
directions: Spread 1/4 cup of vanilla frosting or marshmallow spread or whipped topping into a ghostly shape on top of a graham cracker. Place 2 chocolate chips for eyes.

title: batman bars
directions: Combine and pour into well-buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together; do not brown meat.
Cover tightly.
Bake 6 to 8 hours in a 250° oven.
Potatoes may also be added.

title: new potato after 8's
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until barely done.
Cool; peel and cut into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Place potato slices in a bowl; marinate in creme de menthe for several hours.
Remove slices from liqueur, dip in melted chocolate to coat and place on parchment or waxed paper to set.
Press tops with a fork to leave a decorative design.
Chill before serving.

title: artichoke crescents
directions: Press dough on bottom of jelly roll pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top.
Bake 15 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: zippy oyster crackers
directions: With wire whisk, mix together all ingredients except for crackers.
Pour this mixture over crackers, stirring to coat. Place on baking sheets and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 11 to 12 cups.
Use
with soups and salads.

title: hellmann's creamy italian dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients; refrigerate.

title: broiled flank steak(low calorie and heart healthy)
directions: Score flank steak on both sides.
Place in shallow pan.
Blend dressing, soy sauce and lemon pepper.
Pour over steak and cover. Let stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours or overnight; turn several times.
Place steak on rack of broiler pan.
Broil 3-inches from heat for 5 minutes on each side for medium rare.
(This should not be overcooked.)

title: glazed pecans
directions: Grate orange rind.
Squeeze juice out of orange; add sugar. Boil for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over pecans and coat well.
Spread pecans out on flat surface and allow to cool completely.
(Pecans are ready when glaze has turned cloudy or stickiness is gone.)

title: shoe peg vegetable salad
directions: Heat to boiling:
vinegar, oil, celery seed and sugar.
Cool. Pour over drained veggies.
Let stand overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: low-fat apple pancakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix all liquid, then mix both together. Whip it.
Put nonstick spray on hot pan.
Cook a little and then put nuts on top.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: orange sherbet float
directions: Turn orange sherbet into a large punch bowl.
If sherbet is very hard, let stand to soften.
Add orange juice and ginger ale. Stir to blend.
Makes about 75 servings.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks (keep 1 tablespoon juice). In a medium bowl, mix pineapple juice, pineapple chunks, oranges, coconut, marshmallows and sour cream. Chill 2 to 24 hours. Sprinkle with pecans before serving.

title: herbed chicken bites
directions: Mix together ingredients except chicken and margarine. Melt margarine. Cut chicken into bite-size pieces. Dip in melted margarine. Roll in crumb mixture. Place on baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and hot sausage.
Add sauce and simmer 1/2 hour.
Combine cheeses, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper for filling.
Pour about 1/2 cup meat sauce on bottom of large pan (large roaster pan or 2 lasagna pans).
Lay 4 or 5 pieces of dry lasagna noodles lengthwise over sauce; leave space for expansion. Spread with cheese sauce.
Alternate until full, ending with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except coconut and flavoring. Cook slow until thick.
Add 3/4 can of coconut and flavoring. Pour in pie shell.
Add meringue; sprinkle the rest of the coconut on pie.
Put in oven and brown.

title: rot kraut(red cabbage)
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add shredded cabbage to wilt.
Add 1 cup water and all other ingredients.
Cover and cook on low heat 70 to 90 minutes.
Add sugar and wine vinegar before serving.

title: garlic rice
directions: Cook rice with 2 cans of soup.
Mix rest of ingredients with rice and soup. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: rosenmunner cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and butter until fluffy. Add flour and yolk. Shape into olive size balls.
Press center with thumb which has been dipped in egg white.
Fill with jam. Bake 15 minutes until lightly browned around edges.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, brown sugar, butter, egg yolks, spices and salt in a large mixing bowl; beat until fluffy.
Add evaporated milk; mix just until combined.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold into potato mixture.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Top with whipped topping if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix with hands until crumbly.
Form into small balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Mix together Mexican cornbread mix by directions, except use the egg white.
Add chopped bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Pour the meat mixture into the bread mix.
Pour very little canola oil into a skillet.
Pour all your mixture into the skillet.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.
Add cheese.
Put back into oven until cheese melts.
Good with anything.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in casserole and refrigerate overnight. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: salmon ball
directions: Cut onion very fine.
Add a little horseradish.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Shape into a ball or log.
Put in refrigerator to harden.
Roll in parsley flakes.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate cheeses together.
Saute chopped onion in oil until transparent, then add flour and stir over low heat, about 3 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, picante sauce and sugar.
Heat tortillas in hot oil; drain on paper towel. Dip tortillas in sauce.
Fill them with the grated cheese, reserving a small amount of the cheese for topping.
Roll up the enchiladas and put them in a baking dish.

title: chinese chicken salad 2
directions: Marinate chicken in teriyaki sauce. Bake or fry chicken until done. Cool. Remove bones and shred chicken into long strips.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together for pie crust.
Mix the next 5 ingredients and pour on pie crust.
Top with pie filling.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger with green peppers, then blend in soup and milk. Combine with cooked noodles and bake 46 to 60 minutes at 350°. Do not alter any of these ingredients.
It takes this combination for the special flavor.

title: george rector cakes
directions: Soak bread in milk until saturated.
Add egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix into ground meat.
Form into 4 patties. Dredge patties in flour.
Fry in oil until well done.
Make sauce of drippings, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Serve sauce over patties.

title: minnesota cabbage rolls
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper, rice, onion and 1 can tomato sauce. Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water for 4 minutes; drain. Place portions of meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf. Roll up, folding ends over. Place seam side down in skillet. Mix remaining tomato sauce with brown sugar and lemon juice. Pour over cabbage rolls. Simmer, covered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours; baste often.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Heat liquid drained from the crushed pineapple with enough water to make 3 cups.
When hot, not boiling, pour over lemon jello.
Add sugar and stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Let cool and fold in the other ingredients.
It may be served with mayonnaise thinned with cream or whipped cream.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Place yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in the warm water; let stand.
Heat milk to lukewarm.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and corn oil; mix well.
Add flour, 2 cups at a time; let stand 10 minutes. Make into rolls and let stand 30 minutes.

title: crackerjack
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients over medium heat to 260° on a candy thermometer (hard ball stage).
Working quickly, pour over the popcorn and mix well.
Spread corn flat on a cookie sheet and bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring 3 times during the baking. Makes 3 quarts of Crackerjack.

title: supreme cheese cake
directions: Whip the egg whites and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add 1 cup sugar and cream cheese to egg whites.
Make graham cracker crust.
Pour cream cheese mixture in crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated beef stew
directions: Combine oil, onions, carrots, garlic, wine, bay leaves and pepper to form marinade.
Place beef in stainless steel bowl and pour half of marinade over beef.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Turn meat once during marinating process.
Save rest of marinade in refrigerator for future use.

title: linguini with red clam sauce
directions: Wash clams; place in Dutch oven with 1/4 cup of wine and steam until clams open.
When opened, place clams and their juice in bowl and set aside.
Place oil and garlic in Dutch oven and cook garlic until brown.
Add all other ingredients except linguini and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add clams and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Cook linguini and serve with clam sauce.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Put powdered sugar on top while warm.

title: broccoli and lima bean casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and lima beans (in separate pans) as package directs.
Combine soups and heat, then in a casserole dish, put a layer of lima beans and then a layer of broccoli.
Pour half of the heated soup over this.
Then again, add layers of beans and broccoli. Top with remaining soup.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top of soup.
Crumbs can be Rice or Corn Chex or crackers.
Rice Chex is good!
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour pork(or any cooked meat)
directions: Slice cooked pork or use any leftover meat.
Place meat in mixture of all ingredients and marinate for several hours in refrigerator.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Will keep for several days.
I used fruit in lite syrup or natural.
Also used unsweetened strawberries.
Pie filling is only sugar.

title: low-fat tortilla chips for dips
directions: Spray one side of each tortilla with cooking spray.
Liberally sprinkle each with seasoning blend.
Cut into eighths and arrange seasoned side up on lightly oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes until crisp and very lightly browned.
Do not overbake.

title: chinese noodles with steak and vegetables
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook noodles until tender, but still firm, 4 to 6 minutes.
Drain and rinse under cold water; drain well.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix in saucepan oleo, cocoa, hot water and shortening.
Stir until rolling boil.
Pour over first three dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake on greased 11 x 16-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Ice immediately from oven.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Sear chops in shortening; place in broiler pan.
Top each chop with rice, tomato, green pepper, and onion slices.
Pour water in bottom of broiler.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: snappy cheese wafers
directions: Cut oleo into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Mix in cheese, cayenne and salt.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Make small balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with bottom of small glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, oil and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Mix well and add nuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Pinch into 1-inch balls and press on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.
Can be stored in airtight container in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: zucchini-cheddar quiche
directions: In pie shell, arrange cheese, zucchini and onions in bottom. Beat eggs slightly in bowl, using a rotary beater. Add evaporated milk and salt; blend well. Pour over mixture in pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 25 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between the center and edge comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. This is delicious served cold.

title: lorraine's sour cream drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to cream mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: christine maass' broccoli with rigatoni
directions: In a heavy skillet over medium heat, heat olive oil and butter.
Gently saute the garlic.
Add the broccoli florets and stir gently until pan gets very hot.
Add chicken broth; cover and simmer just until broccoli is tender/crisp.
Add half the fresh basil and the well drained rigatoni to the skillet; mix thoroughly.
Put on hot serving dish and sprinkle with chopped parsley, pepper, grated cheese and remaining basil.

title: no sugar fruit cake
directions: Drain pineapple and chop the fruit and nuts with 1 cup or more of the flour.
Mix other ingredients in mixer using the pineapple juice for liquid.
Pour over the fruit and mix well.
Cook in two loaf pans for 2 hours at 175°.

title: citrus cooler
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until frothy.
Serve immediately.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all of ingredients.
Make dressing as follows and pour over vegetables.

title: lemon sponge cake
directions: Combine sugar, dash of salt and flour.
Stir in melted butter, lemon peel and juice. Combine milk and egg yolks.
Add to lemon mixture. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell, 9-inch.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: sausage biscuit balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls the size of marbles.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: lady fingers
directions: In a cup, beat egg whites until very stiff.
In a bowl, combine sugar and egg yolks.
Blend thoroughly.
Slowly stir flour and salt.
Add egg whites and vanilla.
Mix well.
Press through a pastry tube into individual fingers on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove sheets to rack.
Sprinkle tops with confectioners sugar.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: reese's squares
directions: Mix together and then pat down in pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over peanut butter.
Cut into squares.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 4 to 5 minutes until thickened. Keep stirred well.
Cool, then add last 5 ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 250° to 275° for 1 hour.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: In a bowl, combine egg salad, macaroni, green pepper, mayonnaise and pimientos. Cover and chill. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Yields 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, and 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Combine cream cheese (softened), margarine, sugar, 2 eggs, flour and vanilla.
Mix together; set aside.
Prepare brownies (cake like).

title: busy day oven stew
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a large casserole or pan with lid, make a layer of 1/2 the beef, then 1/2 the vegetables, then remaining beef and vegetables.
Sprinkle with dried onion soup mix; add bay leaves.
Mix soups and tomato sauce and add.
Cover tightly and bake 6 to 8 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tasty kielbasa and beans
directions: Cut kielbasa into 2-inch sections.
Chop onions and green pepper.
Heat in skillet until onion and peppers are soft, stirring constantly.
Add baked beans and the remaining ingredients.
Simmer with lid on for 15 minutes.
Serve with homemade buns and you got a quick meal.

title: easy freezer ice cream
directions: Churn as directed.
May add sweetened fruits.

title: cheese zucchini bake
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic powder.
Drain.
Wash zucchini and cut off ends.
Do not peel.
Slice.
Cook for no more than 5 minutes in a small amount of boiling water.
Drain.
Grease a baking dish and put a layer of 1/2 of the meat, then 1/2 zucchini and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat the layers.
Mix soup and 1/4 cup water; pour over top.
Refrigerate until ready to bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry pork until almost crisp; add onions and cook until golden brown.
This gives a definite tang to the chowder.
Add potatoes and water; simmer 5 minutes.
Add corn and cook 5 minutes more, or until tender.
Stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Heat slowly
until chowder is piping hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Cool chowder before serving if there's time; reheating improves it.

title: beef-noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions together.
Salt and pepper.
Add other ingredients and pour into casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chewy walnut squares
directions: Stir together egg, brown sugar and salt.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add walnuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cookies should be soft in center when taken from oven.
Leave in pan.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat egg and milk, combine mixtures.
Drop batter from spoon over cabbage and cook 5 minutes uncovered.
Cover and steam 5 minutes or longer.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Defrost dough to room temperature (or 5 1/2 minutes in bag, one loaf at a time, in microwave).
Roll out on floured surface to approximately 10
x 22 inches.
Combine eggs, garlic powder and oregano.
Using 1/3 of this mixture, brush onto dough leaving a dry 1-inch border around.
Place pepperoni slices on egg mixture, then grated cheese; pat down.
Starting with a long side, roll up dough.
Pinch ends under.
Cut in half, then pinch these ends under.
Transfer both to a greased cookie sheet.
Poke tops with a fork.
Brush on remaining egg mixture.
Bake in
350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Cut in 1-inch slices or cool completely, wrap in foil and freeze.
To reheat, bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: almond tea
directions: Steep tea bags in 2 cups boiling water for 10 minutes.
Boil sugar in 4 cups water for 5 minutes.
Combine lemon juice, almond extract and vanilla extract.
Combine tea and sugar mixtures with lemon juice and flavorings.
Serve over ice.
Serves 6.

title: easy apricot chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken; arrange in single layer in casserole dish.
Blend preserves, dressing and soup mix, creating a marinade. Pour marinade over chicken and let stand for best flavor.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, less time for smaller pieces of chicken.
Serve with rice.
Pour gravy over rice when serving, making sure to include the apricot pieces.

title: chocolate eclair cake 2
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Pour on top of crackers.
Put on another layer of crackers, pudding and crackers.
Melt chocolate icing and pour over top layer of crackers.

title: jack salmon with fried spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven for rolls and fix when rest is almost done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain whole kernel corn of most of liquid.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes with lid on.
Then remove lid and bake another 30 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreos.
Put half of crumbs on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients and put on top of crumbs in pan.
Add remaining half of crumbs on top.

title: ms. rosemary's cookies
directions: Mix oats, flour, cereal, baking soda and powder in one bowl. Mix butter, eggs, vanilla and sugars well.
Add to first bowl. Next, add M&M's, coconut and pecans.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop tablespoon of dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey stir-fry(this tasty dish uses less sugar, salt and fat.)
directions: In a skillet or wok, heat the oil on high heat.
Add the garlic, onion and chicken.
Stir-fry for one minute.
Add Roger Hong's stir-fry sauce.
Cover and cook until chicken is done, approximately 2 minutes.
Add the carrots and broccoli on top of the chicken.
Cover and cook for 1 minute for crispy broccoli. Serve immediately.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars. Add egg and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients. Add to mixture. Add nuts.
Drop on greased pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 minutes. While hot, mash indention in cookie with spoon.
Fill holes with frosting.

title: mother's day chicken and rice
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Pour raw rice in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Salt and pepper chicken pieces and place on top of rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Add water to creamed soup in separate bowl and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry salad
directions: In bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into 9-inch square pan (ungreased).
Make 3 holes in flour and put in water, oil, vanilla and vinegar.
Beat with a fork until mixed thoroughly.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled for a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut bananas and pour the pineapple juice over them. Let set for 2 to 4 hours. Drain. Mix all ingredients. Better if mixed several hours before serving.

title: chicken a la king(serves 6)
directions: In large pot of boiling water, cook pasta 8 to 10 minutes, until tender.
Drain.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave on High 15 or 20 seconds. Beat cream cheese, milk and sugar in bowl with whisk.
Stir in lemon juice and 1 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Spread in bottom over crust.
Press strawberries into cream cheese.
Pour 2 cups milk into bowl; add pudding and mix with whisk.
Let stand 1 minute or until thick.
Add 1 cup whipped topping and spoon over strawberries.
Garnish with a few strawberries.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together in a 13 x 9-inch greased dish.

title: apple slices
directions: Blend flour, lard, salt and sugar until the size of peas.
Put egg yolk into measuring cup and add milk to make 2/3 cup. Bread egg yolk and add to flour mixture. Divide in half, roll out and put on cookie sheet.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Stir in chocolate chips and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pull candy
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Boil until it reaches the hard ball stage, about 253°.
(When dropped by a 1/2 teaspoonful in cold water it forms a soft ball.) Then pour mixture on a marble slab.
Start pulling as soon as candy can be handled. Pull until firm and creamy.
Roll into a roll and cut into bite size pieces.

title: *hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown. Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add soup slowly.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Serves 6.

title: bernie's angel biscuits #2
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water. Sift dry ingredients together. Melt Crisco and add with yeast water to dry ingredients. Mix and knead well. Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter; fold over. Brush with melted butter. Cook at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees; grease bottom of 9X13 pan.
Spread chopped pecans on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle coconut over pecans. Mix German Chocolate cake mix as directed and spread over coconut and pecans.
Melt butter and 8 ounces cream cheese in sauce pan. Slowly add powdered sugar.
Pour over top of cake mix and bake 45 minutes.
Serve plain or topped with Cool Whip and a strawberry.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Layer cooked chicken in baking dish.
Mix butter, crumbs and poppy seed.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle poppy seed mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in water until done.
Cut up butter and cheese into hot grits.
Let stand until melted.
Stir to mix well.
Slightly beat 2 eggs together in 1 cup measure.
Fill cup with milk.
Add milk and egg mixture to grits.
Put all in large shallow buttered baking dish.
Cover with grated sharp cheese and crushed corn flakes, Rice Krispies or bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: all purpose rib rub
directions: Mix in jar.
Rub on ribs the night before or before grilling.

title: picnic pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours. Yield: 8 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough on an ungreased baking sheet, pressing to seal edges and perforations.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion powder, garlic powder and dillweed in a bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Spread over crust.
Layer cauliflower, broccoli, green peppers, celery and carrots over cream cheese layer.
Top with Velveeta cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap; press vegetables gently into cream cheese.
Chill for 4 hours or longer. Cut into squares.
Yields 15 squares.

title: fish cake casserole
directions: Combine soup, onion, water, juice, salt and pepper in saucepan and bring to a boil.
In a large casserole dish, alternate this soup mixture with layers of rice and peas.
Top with 6 fish cakes. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle casserole with grated cheese and return to oven for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: on-the-wing appetizers
directions: Place drums on rack on a foil lined baking sheet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Brush marinade generously on drums.
Place in 350°
oven for about 1 hour or until drums are golden brown and tender, brushing frequently with the marinade.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Combine jello with boiling water; dissolve.
Fold in all at once the strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Turn half of the strawberry mixture into 12 x 8 x 2-inch serving dish and refrigerate until firm.
Gently spoon on sour cream and remaining mixture.
Serves 12.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Coat apples with cinnamon and 5 tablespoons of sugar.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl; add flour, sugar, baking powder.
Add eggs, flavoring, orange juice, and oil.
Beat well.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Alternate the batter and apples, ending with apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes - not less time! Enjoy!

title: jet's icebox rolls
directions: Mix together and bring to boiling the milk, sugar, mashed potatoes, butter and salt.
Let cool and add the yeast, baking powder and baking soda.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Knead and put in refrigerator ("icebox") for 24 hours. Take out and mold into rolls.
Let rise 2 hours (or until doubled in size). Bake in quick oven at 400° until brown, from 7 to 10 minutes. Return unused portion to refrigerator.
Dough keeps about a week.

title: colonial apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in bowl; set aside.
Cream the sugar, Crisco, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat after each addition.
Stir in apples, lemon juice and vanilla; blend well.
Pour in 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Mix 3 packages cherry jello, hot water and cranberries.
Let set until syrupy.
Add sour cream and nuts.
Serves 12.

title: drumsticks with yogurt sauce
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken drumsticks.
Cook drumsticks in margarine in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat until brown on all sides.
Drain.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and dill weed.
Pour broth over chicken.
Add onion.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until juices of chicken run clear.

title: home-canned rotel
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into sterilized pints.
Seal and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.

In medium bowl, combine all ingredients. With electric mixer at medium speed, beat until smooth and blended. Using hands, roll dough into balls, about 1-inch in diameter. Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets (they do not spread). Pat with fork.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until firm and a light brown.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: tomato beef stew
directions: Brown beef in 2 batches in butter.
Remove from pan. Add onions and saute 2 minutes. Add garlic and then wine.
Scrape up browned bits on bottom of pan. Add meat back to pan, then add vegetables, tomatoes (broken up) and seasonings.
Add bouillon and stir to mix. Add tapioca and stir. Cover and cook in oven at 250° to 300° for 6 to 10 hours. Add liquid as needed.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and let soak for 4 hours; then add 2 beaten eggs, mix well.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Add water. Combine sugars, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and flour.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender.
Spoon evenly over apples.
Cover and bake in a preheated moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave golden apple chunks
directions: Place apples in 1-quart microproof casserole.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Crumble over apples.
Dot with butter.
Cook, covered, on High 7 to 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter, milk, and salt to soft ball stage.
Add marshmallow creme, peanut butter, and butter.
Let stand.
Beat until firm.
Add peanuts.

title: chocolate walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy (about 3 minutes).
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in softened butter.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat balls with zesty sauce
directions: Mix together and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove to crock-pot and cover with Zesty Sauce.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add taco seasoning.
Mix well. Layer with vegetables in a large bowl.
Add enough Mullens French dressing to moisten well.
Top with shredded cheese (taco, Cheddar or Colby).
Then top with taco chips, broken into small pieces.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Pare potatoes.
Cook in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain and set aside.
In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp; remove and drain.
Cook and stir onion in bacon drippings until golden brown.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.

title: "punch bowl" cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box; let cool.
While cake is cooling, prepare box of vanilla pudding.
In a large punch bowl, crumble up cake in bottom of bowl.
Next, layer with the following ingredients, being sure to spread evenly:
can of crushed pineapple, prepared vanilla pudding, can of cherry pie filling and Cool Whip on top.
Decorate with maraschino cherries on top.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add soups and oregano.
Add mushrooms; mix all together.
Then top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: baked hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After half hour, dot with 2 tablespoons margarine and buttered crumbs.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients. Add yeast and milk.
Knead to dough.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cutter.
Put close together in pan and bake at 350°. Makes about 30 biscuits.
They keep in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days or freeze well.

title: toffee
directions: Arrange nuts in a single layer on greased foil in a flat, approximately 9 x 13-inch, pan.
Boil sugar, margarine, Karo and water, stirring constantly, to hard crack stage (300° on candy thermometer).
Pour evenly over pecans.
Break up candy bars and place on top to melt and spread.
Let stand several hours for chocolate to harden.
Break into pieces and store in an airtight container.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve cocoa in melted margarine.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, a little at a time. Add sugar and vanilla.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
After cake is done, spread miniature marshmallows on top and melt.
Remove from oven and cool.
Cover with icing.

title: corned beef sandwiches(richmond times dispatch)
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Spread mixture on bottom half of bun, then cover with top half of bun.
Can either be served cold or hot.
To serve hot, wrap each sandwich in aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or microwave. Makes
8 servings.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix well and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until thick and brown on top.
May make a meringue from egg whites, if desired, and top pie.

title: old fashioned butterscotch pie
directions: Brown butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and water; boil until sugar is dissolved.
Combine cornstarch, egg yolks and milk; add to first part.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell while hot.
Makes 1 pie.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and
pineapple in a pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top.
Dot
the	margarine.
Sprinkle
the nuts on. Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: championship chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: banana split salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and milk in bowl, beating well.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until serving time.

title: hot slaw
directions: Cook the dressing until thick and pour over the chopped cabbage.
Serve while hot.

title: heavenly potato casserole
directions: Beat together all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes last.
Mix well and place in baking dish (9 x 12-inch) sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle on top 1 1/2 cups crushed corn flakes or bacon bits.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: dreamy frozen fruit salad
directions: Whip the cream; set aside.
Combine cream cheese and lime juice; beat until smooth.
