Stir in milk, pecans and pineapple. Fold in whipped cream and pie filling.
Place 24 paper cups in muffin tins; spoon mixture into baking cups.
Cover and freeze.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Drain the peppers and let cool just a little.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla, oil, sugar and zucchini.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients (which have been mixed together) and put in two bread loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Nuts or raisins may be added.

title: okra, creole style
directions: Melt bacon fat in frypan.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add okra and cook 5 minutes. Add tomatoes and simmer over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until okra is tender.

title: chewy cookie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts and mix well.

title: cheese soup
directions: Bring water, bouillon cubes and potatoes to a boil for 25 minutes.
Add vegetables and boil for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to a warm setting, add soup and Velveeta, stir, serve, and enjoy. (Sometimes, I substitute 2 bags of frozen broccoli for the California Blend vegetables.)
This makes a lot of soup, but it is easy to cut recipe to half.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, except chocolate chips. Once mixed well, stir in chocolate chips. Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes. Once cooled, remove cake from pan and top with powdered sugar.

title: jello cookies
directions: In small mixing bowl sift flour and baking powder.
Set aside. In large mixing bowl cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth; these cookies may be rolled and cut out in shapes or dropped by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle each cookie with jello powder.
Bake for 13 minutes in 400° oven.
May also add food coloring to cookie dough if desired.

title: layered salad
directions: In a bowl, layer first 8 ingredients in order given.
Chill for 24 hours.
When ready to serve, salt to taste, toss and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: 24-hour salad (vegetable)
directions: Place a thick layer of lettuce in a container. Layer over this, in thin layers, the next 4 ingredients. Seal the entire dish, from edge to edge, with a layer of mayonnaise. Cover this layer with shredded cheese, bacon and a generous sprinkling of Romano cheese. Cover and seal all this tightly for 10 - 24 hours. Do Not Mix before serving. Keep refrigerated. Use foil or Saran wrap to seal container if container has no lid or covering of its own.

title: cauliflower-grape salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and mustard and stir in rest of ingredients just before serving.

title: "mock" indian pudding toll house
directions: Break up wheat biscuits in a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle over salt and cinnamon.
In a separate bowl, beat the two eggs well with a fork.
Add molasses and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over shredded wheat in baking dish.
Mix gently.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with topping:
ice cream, cream or commercial topping.

title: deep dish strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Lightly combine rhubarb and strawberries in large bowl. Sprinkle with lemon juice and food coloring.
In small bowl, combine sugar, tapioca and nutmeg, mixing well.
Toss lightly with fruit just until combined.
Turn into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; dot with butter.
Top with pastry.
Crimp edges, sealing pastry to edge of baking dish.
With a sharp knife, make gash in center for steam vents.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 400° oven.

title: gobs
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Sift in flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cocoa, adding water last.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Sliver dried beef. Crush parsley and onion flakes if necessary.
Mix all ingredients and shape into ball.
Refrigerate.

title: cinnamon crisp
directions: Break crackers on markings and line bottom of cookie sheet. Melt oleo and put in sugar; dissolve over medium heat.
Add nuts. Boil for 1 minute.
Pour over crackers quickly and let cool.

title: hearty chicken pot pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together all ingredients except pastry. Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Place pastry over casserole; crimp edge to seal and cut slits in pastry.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: farm sale barbecue
directions: Brown beef. Add onions and cook until onions are golden brown. Add tomato soup, catsup, mustard and vinegar. Let simmer for 10 minutes or more. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, oleo, onion and eggs and pour over broccoli.
Top with cheese and crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand and serve.
Serves 6.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Blend lime Jell-O with boiling water. Add pineapple. Blend in cream cheese, milk, mayonnaise and nuts. Mix and refrigerate until set.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in skillet until golden brown. Add beef.
Saute until browned.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, cayenne pepper, bay leaves, basil, salt and pepper; mix well.
Simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning, tomatoes, tomato sauce and green chilies.
Mix Ricotta cheese and eggs together. Layer in following order:
meat, Ricotta cheese, tortillas and cheese.
Make 2 layers and finish with the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until warm throughout.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening; add brown sugar, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts and bits.
Pour in greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 48 squares.

title: pineapple chiffon pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and pineapple.
Bring to a boil.
Take off stove and add jello.
Line two pie plates with vanilla wafers. Beat (very cold) milk and fold into mixture as soon as it is cool.
Pour into lined pie plates.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add marshmallow cream and lemon juice. Beat with electric mixer.
A great dip for any fresh fruit!

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Sprinkle salt on shredded cabbage and mix well.
Let stand for 1 hour or more.
Squeeze off excess water from cabbage.
Mix vinegar, sesame seed oil, red and black peppers and garlic powder together.
Pour over cabbage and mix well.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Boil vermicelli 6 minutes; drain.
Add Greek seasoning, olive oil and lemon juice.
Mix well and marinate at least 4 hours. Add ripe olives, pimentos and green onions.
Mix in mayonnaise. Serve at room temperature.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Pour Ranch dressing over chopped vegetables and bacon bits; mix well.
Chill before you serve.

title: poached salmon
directions: In a large skillet, over high heat, melt butter and coat the pan.
Place the salmon, flesh side down and sear (about 2 minutes).
Turn salmon and reduce to medium heat.
Add wine, cover and cook for 4 or 5 minutes.
The salmon will still be very pink inside.
Serve with a little of the liquid drizzled over the fish.

title: dinette cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour square pan.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: swiss tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, celery, onion, olives and cheese; mix thoroughly.
Fold in eggs and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix macaroni, shrimp, pickles, celery and onion.
Toss.
Mix mayo, pickle juice, salt and pepper. Add to macaroni and mix well.
Chill well before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish and line with graham crackers, not crushed.
Mix together pudding mix and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half of the mixture over graham crackers.
Place another layer of crackers and rest of pudding over crackers.
Lay 1/3 of crackers (takes about 3/4 of box).
Frost top layer with fudge frosting and let set all day or overnight.
Refrigerate.

title: apricot and peach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatins in boiling water and set aside. In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in milk until smooth. Stir in gelatin. Add pineapple and mix well. Chill. When mixture begins to thicken, fold in whipped topping. Pour into a 2 1/2-quart serving bowl. Chill at least 2 hours. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheeseburger turnovers
directions: Brown seasoned beef and onion (cook over low heat for about 5 minutes until just lightly browned).

title: strawberry cake dessert
directions: Pour soda pop into yellow cake mix.
(Do not add anything else!)
Mix it up and pour into sheet cake pan.
Preheat oven and cook cake according to directions on box.
(Do not open door during cooking or cake will fall!)
When cake is done, let it cool completely through and through.
After cake has cooled, pour 3 - 4 cups of sweetened strawberries on top of the cake.
Top with cool whip at room temperature so it will spread better.
Chill in the refrigerator.
Enjoy!

title: no name cake
directions: Bake cake according to the instructions on the box.
When cake is done, poke holes in it about the size of your thumb.
Then pour all of the Eagle Brand milk over the cake.
Then pour the complete jar of caramel over the top of the cake.
Put cake in the refrigerator to cool.
When cake is cool, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with Heath Brickle.
Keep refrigerated.

title: "cake-like" corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, oil and egg, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into prepared pan.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and sugar (3 tablespoons); press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: impossible hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pan.
Brown beef and onion; drain. Stir in salt and pepper; spread in plate.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate over meat.
Bake 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake another 5 to 8 minutes.

title: beef stick
directions: Mix spices together and mix gradually with meat, using hands. Refrigerate until next day.
Second day, mix again and refrigerate. On third day, shape into rolls like salami.
Put on broiler rack in broiler pan on bottom rack in oven and bake 8 hours at 140°.
Turn every 2 hours.
Age 3 days.
Can be frozen.
Should be frozen if want to keep because it can spoil.

title: pork chop - potato bake
directions: Slice potatoes in 1/2-inch slices.
Place in a large buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and minced onion.
Brown pork chops in skillet; place over potatoes.
Spread soup over chops.
Pour water over soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.
May substitute different cream soup, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: cashew taffy
directions: Cook all together until cashews are brown, about 10 minutes. After it boils, pour into a greased cookie sheet.
Break into pieces after cooled.
Makes a lot.

title: spinach and artichoke heart casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Mix with cream cheese and margarine while spinach is hot.
Season to taste.
Place layer of spinach in a 2-quart casserole, then a layer of artichokes.
Repeat layers. Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be prepared early and refrigerated or may be frozen.

title: spicy sausage balls
directions: Mix together sausage, egg, bread crumbs and sage.
Shape into 4 dozen balls.
Brown in skillet.
Pour off grease.
Combined and add to meat, catsup and chili sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Refrigerate or freeze. When ready to serve, reheat.
Place in chafing dish.
Serve with cocktail picks.

title: aunt carmen's dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving to allow flavors to mix.

title: pumpkin cake with coffee frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large mixing bowl, mix cake mix, pumpkin pie mix and 2 eggs. Beat at low speed until moistened. Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Add remaining eggs and topping mix. Beat at low speed until moistened and medium speed 3 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 12-cup fluted tube pan. Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan. Cool completely.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash, drain and chop broccoli (heads only).
Mix red onion, pecans, cheese and apples with broccoli.
Toss with mayonnaise and sugar.
Chill and serve.

title: apple cider chicken
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 375°.
Brown chicken 15 minutes on all sides.
Remove.
Lower temperature to 250°.
Combine cider, Cheddar cheese, soup mix, Blue cheese, mustard, ginger, salt and pepper in skillet.
Cook slowly until cheese melts.
Add cabbage, apples and chicken to skillet.
Stir gently.
Cook slowly for 20 to 30 minutes until chicken is tender.
Serves 6.

title: party steak diane
directions: I add a little dry vermouth.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter for 5 to 6 minutes or until smooth.
Add Chex cereal and stir until they are all covered.
Dump small amount of cereal mix into paper bag and add some powdered sugar.
Shake until covered.
Repeat until all cereal has been covered with sugar.
Let dry 10 minutes on cookie sheet.
Serve.

title: "sugar free" rice custard
directions: Fill 4 cup casserole with eggs, sugar, rice and vanilla.
Add milk and bring to about 1-inch from top.
Place in dish in a 9 x 13-inch pan with about 2-inches of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: great depression cake
directions: In large saucepan, simmer the first 3 ingredients for 10 minutes. Cool 10 minutes. Blend together the remaining ingredients and blend both mixtures. Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: whitefish salad
directions: Combine the fish, celery and potatoes.
Season with salt and paprika.
Marinate with French dressing and serve on lettuce. Garnish with strips of pimento.

title: cinnamon walnut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Combine egg, milk, oil and vanilla; blend well.
Add to flour mixture and stir until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in 1 cup walnuts. Spoon into greased pan.
Sprinkle remaining walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan about 10 minutes and then remove from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with fresh strawberries and milk.

title: french fried noodle casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together, reserving some noodles for the top.
Spread mixture into pan; sprinkle reserved noodles on top and bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy-as-pie cheese straws
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add all ingredients and process about 30 seconds or until mixture forms a ball, stopping often to scrape down sides.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Place the oil and butter in a shallow cooking pan (a jelly roll pan is perfect). Place in oven at 375° to melt. Set aside. In a large paper bag, combine the flour and seasonings. Roll the chicken pieces, 3 at a time, in the melted oil/butter mixture, then drop them in the paper bag. Shake to cover. Place on a dish or waxed paper.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix
first 6 ingredients and form into loaves and place in small
loaf pans.
Place loaf pan on an inverted pie pan in Dutch oven.
Bake
one hour or until done.
For a sauce on top of loaves, mix tomato soup, vinegar and brown sugar.

title: shaker pickles
directions: Do not heat vinegar and spices.
Mix all ingredients and pour over onions and cucumbers in a jar.
Place jar in refrigerator. Shake once a day for 6 days.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 months.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Form into 1-inch balls the size of a walnut.
Flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together in a large bowl or bag.
Place biscuit pieces in bag and shake to coat.
Place pieces in a well-greased Bundt pan.
Stir brown sugar into the margarine until well blended and then pour it over biscuits.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Flip pan over and enjoy!

title: garlic lovers caesar salad
directions: You may adjust garlic and anchovies to taste.
Smash garlic and anchovies into a paste, then add remaining ingredients, except lettuce, cheese and croutons.
Toss with lettuce and top with cheese and croutons.

title: iowa brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in syrup by hand.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in flour.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased pan 15 x 10-inches.
(I use a cookie sheet with sides.)
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Sift powdered sugar on top or ice.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Slice, cook and drain 8 large potatoes.
In a saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons butter and add 4 tablespoons flour.
Stir in 2 cups milk.
Stir constantly.
When milk gets warm, add 6 slices American cheese or Velveeta (big chunk).
Stir until thick.

title: tasty chicken tenders
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix cereal, salt and dill. Dip chicken in oil.
Roll in cereal mixture to coat thoroughly.
Place on foil-lined pan. Bake uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is fully cooked.

title: grandma delphia's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Add tomato sauce, whole tomatoes and catsup to browned mixture.
Simmer.
Cook noodles according to package instructions and add to simmered mixture.

title: monkey bread(1 loaf)
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water.
Beat the egg, sugar and salt together.
Combine the yeast and egg mixtures in a large mixing bowl.
Blend in enough flour to make a soft, but manageable dough.
Knead dough about five minutes.
Cover the bowl with a damp cloth and let dough rise until double in bulk, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Roll dough on a floured surface until dough is about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut the dough with a biscuit cutter and dip each cut piece into the melted butter.
Layer these cut, buttered pieces, overlapping them in an angel food cake pan or a Bundt pan. Cover pan with a damp cloth and let dough rise again until double in bulk.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
If bread browns too fast while baking, cover top with foil.
When baked, turn out on a rack to cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar, water and salt until berries pop. Add the jello.
Let stand to congeal.
Add:

title: squash puppies
directions: Slice squash; cook until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 cup coconut, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla. When cake is done, immediately spread this mixture on top.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine the pretzels and butter; bake for 8 minutes at 400° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix the Dream Whip, sugar and cream cheese; put on pretzel crust.
Mix the boiling water, jello and frozen strawberries.
Put on cheese
layer.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening together.
Add sugar gradually, continuing until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg.
Sift flour and soda together.
Mix well.
Drop mixture by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: pizza rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package; cool.
Lightly toss rice with remaining ingredients in large bowl using 1/2 cup dressing; chill.
Just before serving, toss with remaining dressing.
Serves 6.

title: peppermint ice cream cake
directions: Place cereal in large bowl.
Grate or shave 2 Tbsp. of chocolate from candy bar; set aside.
In a heavy sauce pan melt butter and remaining chocolate.
Pour over cereal and stir to coat.
Press into the bottom of a greased 10 inch spring form pan. Freeze for 30 minutes.
Spoon ice cream over crust.
Freeze for 15 minutes.
Spread with whipped topping; sprinkle with shaved chocolate.
Cover and freeze for several hours or overnight.
Top with candy.
Remove cake from freezer 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Remove sides of pan; cut with a sharp knife and serve immediately.
Yields 8 or 10 servings.

title: barbecued venison
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook venison and onion in drippings until meat is browned.
Drain and set aside.
In saucepan, combine catsup, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, 1/2 cup water, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Stir in venison, onion and bacon.
Cover and cook until venison is tender, 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve on rice.
Serves 4.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in rectangular pan (13 x 9-inch) in oven.
Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken.
Place skin side down in hot butter; bake at 425° for 35 minutes.
Turn; bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: edwin barker's fruit cake
directions: Bake in angel food pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Be sure oven is not too hot.)

title: wonton soup
directions: In medium bowl, combine egg, onion, water chestnuts, soy sauce, ginger, sugar, salt, pepper, pork and shrimp; mix well. One at a time, position wonton skins with point towards you. Place 1 rounded teaspoonful of filling in center of each skin. Fold bottom point up over filling, tucking point under filling. Roll once to enclose filling.
Press down on both sides of filling.
Moisten right corner of wonton with water.
Grasp the right and left corners of the skin and bring them together below the filling, overlapping the left corner over the right and pressing to seal.
In large saucepan, heat water to boiling.
Drop wontons into water one at a time, keeping water boiling.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 5 minutes. Remove and rinse with cold water. Drain thoroughly.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Pour mixture into a buttered casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: In a 5-cup blender, combine all ingredients, except ice cubes. Blend at high speed until blended.
Add ice cubes, one at a time. Process at high speed until blended.
Garnish, if desired, with whole strawberries.
Makes 4 servings.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Sift spices, soda and salt with flour.
Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, flour, nuts, cherries and dates.
Drop on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 70 cookies.

title: butterscotch breakfast rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle 1/2 nuts in bottom of pan.
Place rolls into pan, stacking evenly. Over these, sprinkle brown sugar and pudding mix.
Stir cinnamon and sugar together.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Sprinkle the remaining nuts over the top and drizzle with melted butter.
Cover with towel and set in a warm place for 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Chop onion and jalapeno into this. Pour in small can of corn.
Add water enough to make medium stiff batter.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown and drain on paper towel.

title: quick and easy mashed potatoes
directions: Combine water and milk in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil. Remove from heat; stir in potato flakes.
Add cream cheese and remaining ingredients, stirring until blended.
Cover potatoes and keep warm.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Bake in greased dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream together the first 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven or until cracks appear.
(Grease cookie sheet.)

title: hawaiian yams
directions: Slice yams into 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine with pineapple, butter, sugar and cinnamon in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave 4 minutes and stir.
Sprinkle with nuts and brown sugar.
Cook in microwave 2 to 4 minutes more until hot.

title: tasteful pork chops
directions: Spread pork chops generously on both sides with the mustard. Sprinkle salt and pepper, then dredge in flour.
Brown on both sides in the hot oil.
Pour off oil and add soup and water.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Delicious over rice.

title: buck's broccoli casserole
directions: Cut off broccoli stems.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain. Add Cheez Whiz, Ro-Tel, cream of chicken soup and rice.
Stir all together real good.
Put in casserole dish and bake in low oven 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: mock almond roca
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil. Place crackers on foil. Melt butter and brown sugar and cook for 2 1/2 minutes. Pour over crackers and bake at 350° for 5 minutes (no more). Take out of oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Return to oven (oven can be turned off) melt chips and spread evenly. Sprinkle with nuts while warm. Cool and break into pieces.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes and cook covered in boiling salted water until tender.
Remove from water and cool.
Peel potatoes and grate with coarse grater into a bowl.
Blend in sour cream, grated Cheddar cheese, chopped green onions, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well and transfer to a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.

title: canned green beans
directions: String and break beans.
Put beans and other ingredients in a large pan.
Cover with water and cook 20 minutes, after starts to boil.
Fill clean, hot jars and seal.

title: crazy berry pie
directions: Put water and gelatin in a small saucepan.
Place over direct heat and stir until dissolved or mixture is clear.
In medium sized bowl, combine condensed milk and lemon juice.
Stir in gelatin mixture.
Fold in sour cream.
Mix in 1 1/4 cups of the pie filling.
(Add several drops of almond flavoring to cherry pie filling.)
Turn into crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours, then garnish pie top with remaining chilled pie filling.

title: broccoli cheddar soup
directions: Using a steam Dutch oven, use 1 cup water to steam potatoes and carrots.
Cook broccoli until done.
Mix ham, cream of chicken soup and milk together.
Melt butter in broccoli.
Pour all together in pan.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon buttered new potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water, covered, 10 minutes or until tender.
Combine butter or margarine and next 6 ingredients.
Cook this mixture over medium heat until butter melts.
Pour over potatoes and serve.

title: baked chicken with roasted garlic
directions: Roast Garlic:
Cut top off head of garlic; coat lightly with olive oil and bake 30 minutes at 325°; cover and bake an additional 20 minutes until soft.

title: date nut cake
directions: Dredge nuts and dates with small amount of flour.
Set aside. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, beating well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into nuts and dates mixture and stir to mix.
(You may have to use your hands.) Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: cheese savory
directions: Melt oleo and cheese; add flour and pepper.
Stir in pecans. Cool and shape into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill overnight. Slice thin.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Melt margarine and cream with sugar in a large bowl.
Add beaten egg.
Add dissolved yeast in creamed mixture.
Add flour and stir until well mixed.
Place in an airtight bowl and keep in refrigerator to chill.
Drop by spoonful in a well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: crispy chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings into pieces, discarding tips.
In a small bowl, combine melted butter and garlic powder.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin, mixing well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with water.
Stir until smooth.
Grease mini muffin pans and fill about 2/3 full with batter.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Freezes well.

title: plum good cake
directions: Combine all ingredients at once until well mixed.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until cake tester tests dry/done.

title: easy overnight french toast
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir well.
Pour egg mixture into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch dish.
Arrange bread slices in dish over egg mixture, turning once to coat.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a medium skillet over medium heat.
Arrange 4 bread slices in skillet; cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until browned.
Repeat procedure with remaining butter and bread slices.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Serve with syrup.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: ooey gooey chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth.
In a large bowl, mix together remaining evaporated milk, cake mix and butter.
Press half the mixture into the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes or until set.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Set aside.
Blend together milk and egg yolks, then stir into dry ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Continue cooking for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix in coconut.
Pour into prebaked pie shell. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until set.

title: punch for 100 people
directions: Mix everything except ginger ale according to directions on cans and packages.
Freeze a container of punch for ice.
Pour ginger ale over
punch in bowl.
Add frozen punch and serve.

title: beef and cheese dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and sour cream. Stir in the beef, onions, peppers and Worcestershire sauce. Cut the top fourth off the loaf of bread; carefully hollow out bottom, leaving a 1-inch shell. Cube removed bread and top of loaf; set aside. Fill bread shell with beef mixture. Wrap in foil; place on a baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until heated through. Serve with vegetables and reserved bread cubes. Yield: 3 cups.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat dressing, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: coconut cake with frosting
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, oil and egg yolks; mix well. Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla and buttermilk. Sift flour, soda and salt; add to sugar mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased (spray is okay) 9 x 13 baking pan or dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and springs back in center. Remove and cool while making frosting.

title: hungarian stacked baked potato casserole dish(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Boil potatoes (whole) in kettle until medium soft, then strain.
Wait until potatoes cool, then peel them and slice them in circles.
Spread bread crumbs on bottom of casserole dish to prevent potatoes from sticking.
Stack one layer of potatoes to cover bottom of casserole dish.
Slice sausage and layer (one layer) on top of potatoes.

title: gloria's cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all dry ingredients (flour, meal and sugar).
In 1 measuring cup of water, add your mayonnaise and mix well.
Pour your liquid into dry ingredients.
Mix it well.

title: hot cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except dried beef, about 2 or 3 pieces. Mix well until smooth, then roll into a ball. Cut up the pieces of dried beef and roll mixture in beef. Refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: homemade soap
directions: Dissolve lye in water; cool.
Stir in grease, turpentine and Borax.
Stir 10 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in sack or bowl.
Cut each biscuit into 3 or 4 pieces.
Coat each piece with sugar mixture.
Toss into a Bundt or tube pan.
Nuts can be added to bottom of bread.
Melt oleo, stir in brown sugar; pour over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and turn out on plate. May be sliced or picked off piece by piece.

title: chocolate walnut tart
directions: Combine egg and enough cold water to make 1/2 cup total volume. Whisk knife blade in food processor.
Add flour and 1 square of chocolate.
Blend well and add 1/2 cup margarine.
Pulse 5 or 6 times.
With machine running, add 2 to 3 tablespoons of egg mix until dough ball forms.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Press out into tart pan (an 11-inch one).

title: double chocolate pie
directions: Combine pie filling and milk in a saucepan.
Add butter and chocolate.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour into shell and chill 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping and chocolate curls, if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice by instructions.
Add 1/2 stick of margarine to rice.
Add corn, chicken soup and cheese.
Top with crackers which have been mixed with melted margarine.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: cindy's chicken and rice
directions: Saute chicken breasts in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Remove from skillet.
Take 2 cups uncooked rice.
Put in skillet with 2 tablespoons of butter and saute rice until light.
Add onion and parsley flakes.
Mix together until onion is clear.
Empty into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add bouillon cubes to 3 cups boiling water.
When dissolved, add to casserole dish.
Water should cover rice.
Add in mushrooms.
Mix with rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Bake at 350° until rice is fluffy.

title: manicotti
directions: Boil manicotti noodles until tender; drain and place on foil to cool.
Mix together in large bowl the Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta or cottage cheese and 2 1/2 ounces Parmesan cheese.
Stuff mixture into noodles; place in deep dish pan.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Spread remaining Parmesan cheese on top and the Hunt's spaghetti sauce.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, syrup, water and salt to a boil.
Add peanuts. Cook until peanuts stop popping or syrup turns light brown. Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Stir rapidly until mixture foams.
(Will foam over if not careful.)
Pour on greased pans and smooth out quickly.
Break into small pieces when cool.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute butter, carrots, onion and zucchini until tender. Pour into
baking
dish.
Add mushroom soup and sour cream and mix. Top
with
buttered
croutons
and	bake
at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: microwave sauced meatballs
directions: Stir together egg, milk, onion, salt and bread crumbs.
Add meat; mix well.
Shape into 36 meatballs.
Place in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Micro-cook, uncovered, on High for 5 to 9 minutes, rearranging meatballs and rotating the dish a half turn once.
Drain off fat.

title: veggie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Unroll crescent dough and spread onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Add dressing mix.
Spread on cooled baked crescent dough. Top with chopped vegetables.
Chill overnight and cut into bars.

title: gramma's graham cracker cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add beaten egg yolks, milk and graham crackers, rolled fine with the baking powder, a little salt and vanilla.
Add egg whites and walnuts.
Cook in layer tins for 1/2 hour.
Best served with whipped cream.

title: blue damson pie
directions: Cook damsons with sugar and a little water (up to halfway of plums in pan).
Cook until done.
Remove from heat and add flour or tapioca, butter and beaten eggs.
Pour into pie crust and top with pie crust.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes, then lower oven temperature to 350° and bake about 35 minutes more.

title: linda's "angry chicken on pasta"
directions: Cut breasts into bite-size cubes.
Place in a plastic bag with 1/2 of the minced garlic and crushed red pepper flakes. Refrigerate for several hours, or overnight.
(Best flavor if you don't skimp here, but you can cook right away, too). Slowly saute the remaining garlic and red pepper flakes in olive oil to flavor your oil.
Be careful not to burn the garlic.
Add your onion slices and cook until tender.
Saute your chicken in batches, being sure to cook thoroughly.
You may have to add oil from time to time.
Drain well.
Throw all the chicken into the pan; add your cooked onions and heavy cream.
Heat through.	Serve over cooked pasta and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: oven frying
directions: Brush chops, chicken (skinned), shrimp or fish with the egg substitute, then roll in any one of the ingredients and cook in oven without turning.

title: cranberry whip
directions: Grind whole cranberries in the blender.
Pour in a bowl.
Add sugar and let set 1 hour.

title: great punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Add juices; mix well. Chill several hours before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ketchup.
Form into a loaf.
Cover the bottom of baking dish with ketchup.
Place loaf in dish.
Bake for 1 hour in preheated 350° oven.
The meat and ketchup juices make a good sauce to serve over meat loaf.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Combine sliced cucumbers and green onions in bowl.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers and refrigerate several hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and ginger.
Mix all ingredients together; chill 4 to 5 hours.
Roll out on floured cookie sheet.
Cut with cookie cutter or water glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Whip cream cheese and whipped topping together.
Add the 1/4 cup cherry juice.
Add rest of ingredients.
May add nuts if desired.
This must be chilled.
Can be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: tomato sauce cake
directions: Cream together butter
and
sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix tomato sauce and water.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture
alternately
with
tomato sauce.
Pour into greased pan; bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: foley's chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate overnight or at least several hours.
Bake on sheet pan in marinade at 350 F for 45-60 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil brown sugar
and
cream.
Test by dropping in cold water (soft ball).
Put on top of icing the black walnuts.

title: sticky buns
directions: Put frozen rolls in a greased 9 X 13 pan.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar, pudding, milk and cinnamon.
Pour over frozen rolls. Top with nuts.
Let raise over night.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: creme fraiche
directions: Gradually add whipping cream to sour
cream.
Add sugar and vanilla and whisk until thoroughly blended.
Chill.
Whisk again just before using.
Makes 2 cups.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Combine the cranberries, oranges, apples, pineapple, sugar and nuts and mix well.
Fold fruit mixture into gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold sprayed with vegetable spray.
Chill until set.
May be made day ahead.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar together.
Combine pudding and milk; mix well.
Blend pudding and cheese mixture and fold in Cool Whip.
Crush Oreo cookies and spread half in the bottom of a large bowl, casserole dish or a clean plastic flower pot.
Add mixture and top with remaining crushed Oreos.
Top with gummy worms and plastic flowers.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef in olive oil.
Drain.
In blender mix canned tomatoes
and
water.
Pour
in
large Dutch oven.	Add potatoes, onion, ground beef, Worcestershire and chili powder. Add salt
and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook for 1 hour.

title: tater casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes, until done.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Beat the shortening, sugar and egg.

Sift the sifted flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Stir in alternately with the milk. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in muffin cups which have been lined with papers. While still hot, roll in 6 tablespoons melted butter and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Best served hot.

title: roncho beans
directions: Fry onions in oil until golden; add ground beef and fry with onions until all redness in meat is gone.
Add all remaining ingredients except onion rings.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
During the last 10 minutes of baking, top with onion rings.
Bake in all about 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: punch bowl trifle
directions: Add 2 cups boiling water to jello.
Set aside to cool and add frozen strawberries to the hot water.
Stir as needed.
Prepare pudding according to instructions on box.
Layer ingredients in punch bowl as follows:
first layer of cake, second layer of strawberry jello, third layer of vanilla pudding (thin layer) and fourth layer of Cool Whip (thin layer).
Repeat layers 3 times, ending with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and cover with wrap until served.
Serves many.

title: geoff's favorite pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread garlic on pizza crust.
Top with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle with green pepper, tomatoes, corn and olives, using as much as you like!
Bake for about 8 minutes, until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: old fashion cole slaw
directions: Blend all ingredients and whip lightly for 1 minute thoroughly.
Pour over shredded cabbage, about 1 quart.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Dice chicken.
Combine cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup in a large saucepan. Follow directions on can.
When this begins to boil, stir in Cheez Whiz and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bring to soft boil.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil and get hot enough for sugar to dissolve.
Cool before using.
Drain all of your beans and add celery, onion, green peppers and pimento.
Pour your liquid mixture over all your ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
This is great for picnics and church dinners. Can be made days in advance and will keep for weeks.

title: society sweet chip pickles
directions: Prick both ends of cucumbers with darning needle and place in gallon crock.

Pour boiling water over for 4 mornings, draining off old water each time. On the fifth morning, drain and cut large cukes into 1/4-inch slices (cut small cucumbers into 1/2-inch chunks) and return to crock.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix glaze and strawberries together and set aside.
Combine cream cheese, milk and powdered sugar.
Add cake pieces and Cool Whip.

title: zucchini
directions: In a 10-inch iron skillet, spread margarine on bottom and sides.
Slice zucchini 1/4-inch thick and lay in pan.
Slice onion on top of zucchini.
Slice tomatoes on top of onion.
Salt and pepper on top.
Add enough water to almost cover.
(If using frozen zucchini, use only a small amount of water.)
Cover with lid.
Cook on medium heat on top of stove until bubbles, then turn burner on low heat.
Cook until tender.
May need to add water before done.
When done, add cheese.
I serve in skillet.

title: pork chops indonesian with rice
directions: In skillet, brown chops in oil.
Remove and drain fat.
Drain peaches and reserve syrup.
Blend syrup, sugar, onion, soy sauce, ginger, mustard and garlic powder.
Add syrup mixture to chops. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Add green pepper strips and peaches.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Toss sugar, meal and flour together.
Add unbeaten eggs, butter and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Bake at 375° until filling is set.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes and grate, preferably with hand grater.
Grate in onion.
Add baking powder, salt and flour.
Stir to make a batter.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Drain liquid from grated cucumber and discard.
Mix pulp and all other ingredients until well blended. Refrigerate until served.

title: old-fashioned chicken salad
directions: Stew hen and cut up in large pieces with no skin, enough for 2 cups.
Marinate chicken lightly with French dressing at least 1 hour.
Drain off dressing.
When ready to serve, combine with celery and mayonnaise (enough to coat chicken).
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place on platter.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with fresh parsley.
Also good served cold in fresh whole tomatoes.

title: jamaican jerk chicken
directions: *I just use "Trappey's" peppers.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Prepare pudding; mix in buttermilk and stir well.
Add unsweetened fruit. Mix with Cool Whip and nuts.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring rice to a boil.
Drain and let sit.
Cut off heads of broccoli from stalk, dice both stack and head.
Cut block of cheese into squares or slices. Mix together in a large bowl and add salt and pepper to taste.
Place into a baking dish and cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with additional cheese while still hot.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Arrange meaty side of chicken up in casserole.
Place cheese on top of chicken.
Combine soup and wine and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour half of mixture in container and let chill until firm.

title: popeye spinach squares
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Place in a greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Place bread and sausage in a 10x13 inch baking dish. Mix all other ingredients and spread over the top of the bread and sausage mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. May be prepared and refrigerated uncooked the night before.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in dissolved Jell-O and chill.

title: cookout corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; chill.
Stir before serving.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Marinate up to 2 pounds of meat for at least 6 hours.

title: squash casserole(serves 6)
directions: Cut squash into pieces and cook with small onion until tender. Drain and mash.
Add eggs (beaten) and milk.
Stir in shredded Cheddar cheese.
Pour into greased casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Combine beef, water, salt, oregano, marjoram, peppercorns and bay leaves.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove the beef.
Cut meat from bones and cut up meat. Strain broth; skim excess fat.
Return broth to kettle.
Add prepared vegetables and meat.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Serves 10 to 12.

title: biscuits from "thacker's christmas tree inn"(carrysville, tennessee)
directions: Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch to 3/4-inch and cut with cutter (or glass).
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 15 to 18 biscuits.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into large pizza pan, sealing all seams. Top with cooked and drained sausage, potatoes, eggs and cheese. Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes until crust browns and eggs are set.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients except grease to make a stiff dough. Heat grease to abut 375°.
Drop dough by teaspoon into hot grease and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease (1 dozen) muffin tin. Stir together bran and milk.
Let this mixture stand for 10 minutes.
Melt margarine and combine with molasses and egg.
Add margarine mixture to soaked bran and blend well.
Add all remaining dry ingredients and beat briefly.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon batter into muffin cups and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: reuben roll-ups
directions: Separate crescent rolls. Snip sauerkraut. Add the dressing and mix.

Layer the corned beef, cheese and 2 tablespoons sauerkraut mixture on the wide end of the crescent triangle. Roll up, beginning at wide end. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 8.

title: jello, pineapple and cream cheese salad
directions: Bring to boil can of crushed pineapple.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Add cream cheese and 1/2 cup water.
Mix well and place in the refrigerator until it starts to set.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt.
Add egg yolks.
Add about 1/3 cup milk.
Mix well.
Add the rest of milk and vanilla. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add butter.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the sugar and flour.
In saucepan, bring to a boil the butter, water, oil and cocoa.
Pour on dry ingredients and stir well.
Add eggs, soda, milk mixture and vanilla.
Stir and pour into well-greased cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
While cake is warm, make frosting.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed and drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain again.
Mix mayonnaise, salt and sugar.
Combine with macaroni and remaining ingredients.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Place first four ingredients (sugar, margarine cocoa and milk) in saucepan and bring to boil.
After reaching a rolling boil, boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the peanut butter, oats, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop onto wax paper to cool.

title: wagon wheel cookies
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and vanilla.
Blend in melted chocolate and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients together; stir into chocolate mixture.
Add walnuts.
Chill several more hours or overnight.

title: low-fat oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg whites.
In a medium sized bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to sugar mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and vanilla.
Chill one hour.
Preheat oven to 350°. Roll a teaspoon of the dough into a ball and place on the ungreased sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes about 55 cookies; 1 gram of fat per cookie.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Dice onion; cut up cabbage.
Cover bottom of iron skillet with grease.
Mix all ingredients; cover. Cook on medium-low heat until done, stirring often.
Water may be added if needed.

title: noodle kugal
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add to noodles.
Add melted butter and mix.
Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: acadian blueberry grunt
directions: Boil berries, water and sugar in a large saucepan, covered, until there is plenty of juice.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter and shortening, then add enough milk to make a soft biscuit dough.
Drop by tablespoons onto hot blueberry sauce.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes without peeking.
Serve from saucepan.
Cream may be added.

title: sour cream topping
directions: Combine sour cream, butter, egg and sugar in a saucepan.
Beat with eggbeater slightly.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Stir in pecans, if desired.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: In large kettle, cook ribs until tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Skim off foam.
Remove ribs, strain broth and refrigerate.
Remove meat from bones, set aside.
When cool, skim fat from broth. Return to heat.
Add potatoes, carrots, salt and pepper; simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add sauerkraut, sausage and rib meat; simmer until heated.
Meanwhile, cook bacon until crisp, drain and crumble.
Discard all but one tablespoon of the drippings.
Cook onion in drippings until tender (can use oleo).
Add onions to soup; simmer 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Add bacon and serve.
Yields 3 quarts.
It's delicious.

title: hot cheddar crackers
directions: Lay crackers out on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and dash of red pepper.
Heat oven to 350°.
Melt cheese on crackers.
Serve hot.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Crush the Oreos into fine crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Soften ice cream.
Spread evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle peanuts on top and freeze.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add ingredients.
Simmer 4 to 8 hours.

title: jewish cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients together on medium speed of mixer.
Pour into a spring-form cake pan and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes. Then brown top in your broiler.
Watch carefully, as it will brown quickly.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter, and 3 tablespoons of sugar in bowl.
Press evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch lightly greased pan (Pam is okay).
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool completely. With electric mixer, beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until creamy.
Beat in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture over cooled pretzel crust.
Pour boiling water into bowl and stir in Jell-O until well dissolved.
Add strawberries to Jell-O and cool until syrupy. Pour over cheese mixture and chill for 3 to 4 hours before cutting into squares.

title: christine's chicken with spaghetti
directions: Place chicken breasts in a glass pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken.
In small saucepan brown onion and garlic in olive oil.
Pour over top of spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle Romano cheese on top.
Put in oven for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Prepare pasta and serve chicken and tomato gravy over pasta.

title: orange-carrot congeal salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water together.
Let cool some.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Put in mold or large bowl and refrigerate until congealed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Do not overcook.
Cool.
Add eggs.
Add some onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Stir lightly.
Can be made the day before.

title: spring corn
directions: Cook corn as directed on package.
Saute onions in butter. Add corn, sugar, mustard, parsley and salt and pepper.
Mix and serve.

title: caramel coffee treat
directions: Add 1/4 cup caramel topping to a large coffee cup. Finish filling with fresh coffee.
Add creamer to taste. Top with Reddi-Wip and a sprinkle of cinnamon. Yum!

title: cream candy
directions: Use enamel pan only to cook in.
Boil all ingredients to hard boil stage.
Do not stir after mixture starts to boil.
Pour on cold marble slab (buttered).
Knead like dough for a few minutes. When it becomes cool enough to handle, pull until white and then cut with scissors.

title: burger cabbage casserole
directions: Saute burger in oil until lightly browned.
Mix in onion, salt and rice; cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add tomato soup and water. Mix thoroughly and remove from heat.
Put cabbage in casserole. Pour burger mix over cabbage to completely cover (do not stir). Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: puppy chow candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo.
Pour over cereal, stirring to coat.
Put powdered sugar in sack and mixture to coat and shake.

title: asparagus-tomato quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 10-inch pie shell 10 minutes. Beat eggs with next 4 ingredients. Stir in cheese. Chop asparagus for bottom of pie shell.
Pour in liquid. Bake 20 minutes. Arrange asparagus and tomato on top (pinwheel design). Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pork chop and stuffing casserole
directions: Lightly brown chops in oil in large glass ceramic skillet; remove chops and sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook onions in drippings 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in stuffing mix and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Combine soup with water.
Add chopped apples, squash and diluted soup to stuffing; stir lightly to combine. Place in large skillet; then place chops on top.
Cover with foil. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.
A serving for 6.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in water for 10 minutes; drain.
Melt butter. Add flour to make a smooth paste.
Add milk; cook until thick. Add salt, pepper and cheese; mix well.
Place cabbage in buttered baking dish.
Pour sauce over; top with crumbs.
Bake at 375° until bubbly and brown, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: egg and sausage quiche
directions: Brown, drain and cool sausage.
Beat eggs and milk, add salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Mix well; add bread, cheese and sausage. Pour in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove 1 hour before baking.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix soup, chilies, spices, Tabasco and chicken broth.
Blend well.
Cover bottom of large casserole with 1/2 of the Doritos, 1/2 chicken, then 1/2 soup mix and 1/2 of the cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix softened margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar until blended and set aside.
Whisk pudding, milk and vanilla until blended.
Whisk in Cool Whip, then whisk in cream cheese mixture. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer Oreos, mixture, Oreos, mixture, etc. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Skin chicken and bone.
Put chicken in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup with lemon juice and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Combine poppy seed with crushed crackers and sprinkle over soup mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake 30 minutes until bubbly, at 350°.

title: corn bread dressing(for chicken or turkey)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes, covered.
Bake uncovered for 10 minutes longer in a 350° oven.
(This amount of dressing can be used to stuff a 5 to 6 pound bird.)

title: tart lemon-cheese cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Combine water and milk in a small bowl; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, and salt; add to butter mixture alternately with milk mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed after each addition until blended.
Stir in rum flavoring.
Beat egg whites at high speed until stiff peaks form; gently fold into batter.
Pour batter into three greased and floured 9 inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans completely.
Spread lemon-cheese filling between layers and on top of cake.
Spread lemony white frosting on sides.
Garnish with lemon slices, if desired.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter in double boiler.
Pour over cereal and mix.
Add powdered sugar and toss to coat.

title: potatoes and ham casserole
directions: Dice potatoes, salt and boil until done.
Chop onion very fine and spread in large square casserole dish.
Drain most of the water from pot.
Pour rest of the water and potatoes into dish.
Cover with foil and let set until cool.
Then spread thin layer of mayonnaise over potatoes.
Sprinkle black pepper and ham (cut into small pieces) over potatoes.
Grate cheese and layer on top.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Mix together and form into small balls (1 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli spears in boiling water.
Drain and arrange in 9 x 12-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Cook chicken, cut into bite-size pieces and arrange over broccoli.

title: onion-tomato soup
directions: Peel and thinly slice onions.
In a large saucepan, saute onions in butter.
Add tomatoes, beef broth, basil, salt and pepper.

title: peanut logs
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in large pan; heat until sugar dissolves.
Stir in peanut butter and margarine.
Mix well until melted.
Add cereals and peanuts.
Mix well.
Press into large cake pan.
Cool and cut into serving pieces.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cut up celery and pimento fine; cream the cheese in mixer and add all other ingredients.

title: pink party salad
directions: Drain pineapple, and mix juice, marshmallows and jello; dissolve over low.
Let cool.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese, nuts and Cool Whip.
Fold in jello mixture.
Chill until set.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar; add peanut butter, beaten eggs, dry ingredients (sifted together) and flour.
Mix well. Shape into balls about size of walnuts.
Place 1 or 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Press with a fork to flatten and mark.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: lemon poppy bread
directions: Mix all ingredients a couple minutes with electric mixer. Pour into 2 loaf pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until middle springs back when touched.

title: real chicken soup
directions: Put chicken and salt into large (12 to 14 cup) soup pot and cover with cold water.
Let it come to a boil and lower heat. Remove all gray matter with ladle strainer so soup water is clear and clean.
Then add all vegetables, dill and parsley.
DO NOT LET SOUP BOIL; it must simmer slowly for about 1 1/2 hours.
This is what produces a clear, sweet broth.
Taste for seasoning.

title: venison roast
directions: Place roast in a large container with vinegar and enough water to cover it.
Marinate for at least 3 hours in the refrigerator. Wash meat thoroughly under cold water to draw the blood out of the meat.
Pat dry and stuff with garlic.
Plug each hole with a little piece of meat.
Salt and pepper roast and roll in flour.
Heat just enough oil to cover the bottom of pan and brown roast on all sides. Sprinkle onion soup mix over roast and add water to make desired amount of gravy.
Baste roast with gravy while cooking slowly in covered pot for approximately 4 hours or until tender.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onions and bell pepper in oil until done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add more pepper and tomato juice and cheeses.
Cook with meat.
Add garlic.

title: vanilla caramels
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, cream and salt in heavy large pan. Place over low heat and stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to 232° (very soft ball), stirring occasionally.
Add butter a little at a time to prevent scorching.
Test often in cold water (240°) to determine the consistency desired in the finished caramels. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: crispy-edged cheddar turkey burgers
directions: Make hamburger type patties and fry in skillet.
When edges look cooked, flip the burgers over and lightly sprinkle with onion salt.
Cook about five more minutes and fill "dent" with cheese. Eat with fork or with fingers if no one is around.

title: chicken bundles with bacon ribbons
directions: Place chicken between two sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; pound to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Place chicken in a large shallow container and set aside.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, water and oil together, then add oranges. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: miami punch
directions: Pour chilled orange or tangerine juice and ginger ale into punch bowl; mix well.
Drop ice cream by the tablespoonfuls into mixture.
Stir until ice cream is almost melted.
Serve.

title: quick cookie bars
directions: Combine oil, eggs, water and vanilla in a 3-quart bowl.
Add dry cake mix and blend by hand.
Add chocolate chips; mix.
Spread evenly in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes (until lightly brown, but don't overbake).
Cool slightly and cut into squares.

title: pork loin marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour half of mixture on pork loin and let sit for 30 minutes.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant;
soak
in
salted water several hours or overnight.
Soak
bread
crumbs in evaporated milk, plus whole milk.
Saute pepper, onions and celery in butter until tender. Boil eggplant
until tender.
Mix all together, except cheese; blend well.
Place
in
greased
casserole;
top
with cheese. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend eggs with milk in large bowl.
Stir in mixture of corn, salt, sugar and margarine.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: muffin brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over medium-low heat; cool. Stir in eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Stir in
nuts.
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 22 to 24.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in corn and eggs, beaten whole.
Drop a tablespoon at a time in hot oil or Fry Daddy.
Cook until golden brown.
Serve hot with syrup or butter.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: First you toast the bread.
Then after a while you put the butter on the toast after the toast pops up.
Then you mix the cinnamon and sugar.
Shake it up real good if you have a container.
After you shake it up real good, you put some cinnamon and sugar on the butter that is on the bread.
There is your cinnamon toast.

title: carrot soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients all together with several thyme leaves.
Put into blender in small amounts.
Add cream cheese in blender.
Add milk or half and half.
You may add 1 teaspoon thyme if leaves are not used.
Very little salt is needed.
Add white pepper.
Serves 24 to 30.

title: cream vegetable casserole
directions: In saucepan, gently cook butter and onion for 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in flour, salt and mustard and then milk. Add pepper, celery and salt.
Arrange layer of drained vegetables, layer of cheese and layer of sauce.
Repeat and end with cream sauce. Top with crumbs and frozen pieces of onion rings.
Bake 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cake cool; pierce with fork and drizzle Kahlua over cake.
Chill overnight.
Break up cake and place half in 3 1/2-quart truffle bowl.
Prepare mousse according to directions. Add a layer using half of pudding.
Crumble 2 candy bars on pudding and cover with 1 tub of Cool Whip.
Repeat process using remaining candy bars as a top garnish.
Chill.
Serves 12.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion.
Cook until tender, but not brown. Add next 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Mix crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Snip parsley over top.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cover and boil over low heat about 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, syrup and all the fruit juices.
Chill thoroughly in your refrigerator.
Just before serving time, ladle punch over ice until well chilled.
Pour in ginger ale.
Makes 24 to 30 punch cup servings.

title: fruit surprise
directions: You will need a Black and Decker shell maker.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and 1/4 cup milk.
Add 2 egg yolks and whip.
Add 1 3/4 cups milk and cook slowly until boils (you may heat the 1 3/4 cups milk in microwave before adding, hot not boiling).
Add 1/2 stick oleo and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually add 4 tablespoons sugar.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread on pie. Bake 15 minutes or until brown at 450°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and molasses for 1 minute.
Add soda; stir and pour quickly over popped corn.
Mix until coated.
Place on baking sheets.
Bake in 225° oven for 45 minutes; stir every 15 minutes.
Pour out on wax paper; cool.
Separate and store in airtight container.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Separate chicken breasts into cutlets and sprinkle them with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter until transparent.

Remove from pan. Dip chicken in flour and saute in melted butter in same pan on each side until golden brown. Add mushrooms and onion mixture and wine. Cover and simmer over low heat 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with wild rice.

title: beef stew
directions: Put in crock-pot and simmer approximately 8 hours.

title: hoe cake
directions: Cut shortening into flour and add milk, a little at a time. Work dough with a heavy spoon.
Roll dough about 1/3 of an inch thick and place on a cookie sheet.
Mark 2 inch squares for lazy biscuits or leave plain for hoe cake.
Bake in a 450° oven about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: rotten coconut cake
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar, and coconut together and refrigerate overnight.	Bake cake in two 9 inch round cake pans.
Cool.
With a fork punch holes in the tops of the cake.
Spread coconut mixture over top of bottom layer.
Place top layer on bottom layer.
Spread coconut mixture on top.
Frost entire cake with Cool Whip.	Sprinkle cake with additional coconut if desired.
For best results, after frosting, refrigerate cake for at least 12 hours or overnight.

title: cock and bull stew
directions: Combine steak sauce, bouillon, salt, pepper, sugar, and hot water in crock pot; stir well. Add remaining ingredients except flour, mix carefully. Cover and cook on low setting for 7 to 10 hours or on high for 4 hours. To thicken gravy, make a smooth paste of flour and 1/4 cup of juices from stew. Add to crockpot. Cover and cook on high setting until gravy is thickened.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Mix together soups and milk.
Add this mixture to the rice. Place in oblong baking dish.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture. Cover with foil and cook until tender at 350°, for approximately 1 hour.

title: mustard french bread
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine the mayonnaise and the mustard.
Spread onto one side of the bread slices.
Sprinkle tops with parsley and Parmesan cheese.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until done; drain and let cool.
Cook hamburger and onion until done.
Add garlic, sweet basil, pepper, salt, tomato sauce and tomato paste; simmer for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs and add to cottage cheese.
Stir well.
Start with meat sauce (about 3/4 cup).
Lightly cover bottom of pan, then layer with noodles and cottage cheese mixture.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Do this until pan is full.
Cover to the top with meat sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Spread over a 12-inch pizza pan or similar dish.
Add a layer of each of the rest of the ingredients in the order given.
Cover and chill until ready to serve with crackers.

title: polynesian cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan or spray well with Pam.
Throw all ingredients in bowl.
Don't bother to sift flour.
Mix with a spoon, not a mixer.
Pour into baking pan; bake 50 minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix soup, milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1 cup of cheese and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes.
Open rolls into a large rectangle and cut into 3 strips.
Place the strips across to form lattice top and bake for 15 minutes, uncovered.
Spread remaining cheese and onions on top and bake, uncovered, for 3 to 5 minutes, until the cheese melts and the onions turn brown.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all together (except corn chips).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with 1 cup crushed corn chips.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: walnut streusel muffins
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and sugar; cut in butter to form crumbs in medium bowl.
In small bowl, combine 3/4 cup of the crumbs and 1/4 cup walnuts; set aside.
Into remaining crumbs, stir in remaining 1 cup flour, baking powder, spices, baking soda, salt and remaining 3/4 cup walnuts.
Combine sour milk and eggs and stir into dry ingredients.
Spoon into lined muffin tins.
Fill 2/3 full.
Top each with a generous spoonful of crumb mixture. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: nut cake
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl; mix well.
Stir in nuts and mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini(italian style)
directions: Select young, small zucchini.
Wash but do not pare.
Cut in 1-inch slices.
Slice onion and saute in butter until yellow; add zucchini and cook and stir for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and season with salt, pepper and sugar; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Put in buttered baking dish, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Serves 4.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in flour, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape in crescents and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: apricot bread
directions: Beat together eggs and mashed bananas until creamy.
Add water, vanilla and oil and beat.
Measure flour, soda and baking powder.
Beat well.
Stir in chopped apricots.
(These must be chopped very fine in order for them to blend into batter.)

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add the milk and set aside.
Saute 1/2 pound ground meat until brown.
The next 3 ingredients are prepared ahead to be ready to be used:
1 large onion, finely chopped, 1/2 pound cheese and 4 jalapeno peppers, chopped fine (fresh or canned).

title: watergate salad
directions: Put pineapple in bowl and mix pudding in.
Fold in Cool Whip. Add nuts, if desired.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Mix well first 3 ingredients and pour this into a deep pan. Mix well the next 3 ingredients and roll out into a large, flat circle.
Next, mix the cocoa and 3 cups sugar together.
Place half of it on the dough.
Roll the dough up and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place the pieces in the pan on the syrup base.
Place a pat of butter on each piece.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine milk, lemonade and food coloring (if desired). Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Garnish with lemon slices and mint
if desired. Chill until served. Serves 6-8.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out baked pulp, being careful to keep skin in one piece.
With wire whip, beat potatoes with cottage cheese, milk and onion; spoon mixture into skins.

title: ice tea
directions: Place in pot on stove with water. Bring to a rolling boil. Let set for 5 minutes. Put 1 cup sugar in pitcher and mix while tea is hot. Let set and pour in glasses over ice.

title: date muffins(makes 12 muffins.)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups or use paper baking cups.
Mix baking mix, sugar, egg and water; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Stir in dates.
Fill in muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Cut in small pieces.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with flour tortillas.
Mix onion, Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of chicken soup and chicken broth in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Pour sauce over dish.
Cover with grated cheese. Cover with aluminum foil while baking.
Bake until it bubbles.

title: fruit delight(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients and eat.
Stays good in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients with fork in pie pan.
Press into pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°
or until brown.
Fill with favorite filling.

title: oyster artichoke soup
directions: Boil fresh artichokes in saltwater with vinegar for 55 minutes or until tender. Drain and cool. Scrape leaves and chop. Set aside. In a large Dutch oven, brown flour in butter and oil for 5 minutes. Add onion, celery, green onions and garlic. Saute for 15 minutes. Add parsley, ham, turkey or chicken stock, season salt and pepper; simmer 20 minutes. In another pan, heat oysters in their liquid until edges curl. Drain off liquid into soup mix. Cut up oysters or leave whole. Add to soup and simmer 15 minutes longer. Season to taste. Serves 12.

title: deep fried fish fillets
directions: Rinse fillets off well in cold water; drain off excess water. Roll fillets in flour.
Make mixture of the egg and milk.
Dip floured fillets into this mixture, then roll in Italian seasoning. Place in deep fryer; fry until golden brown and float on top of oil.

title: cherry tomato sour cream dip
directions: Wash tomatoes and leave stems on.
In a small serving bowl, combine sour cream with the rest of the ingredients.
Refrigerate, covered, along with the tomatoes, about 1 hour or until well chilled.
Place dip in center of large tray, surrounded with cherry tomatoes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place cucumbers and onions in large pot.
Sprinkle pickling salt over cucumbers and onions.
Cover with water.
Stand for 3 hours.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar, turmeric and mustard seed together.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Seal hot.

title: seafood lasagna(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using a medium saucepan, mix the milk with the water and heat over medium heat.
