Sprinkle with enough paprika to make the sauce pale pink; add nutmeg and salt to taste. Mix the vermouth and flour together in a small bowl to make a smooth paste.
Whisk this into the milk, stirring constantly, until the sauce thickens, and then set it aside.
Heat a nonstick skillet and coat with a nonstick vegetable oil spray.
Add scallops and garlic, sprinkle with salt and pepper, and cook until the scallops just turn solid white.
Remove from the skillet and combine with the crab.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Drain and mix canned fruits, saving juices.
mix 1 cup drained pineapple juice, (add others if not one cup) with instant pudding and Tang.
Pour over fruits.
Chill overnight.
Slice and add bananas just before serving or the flavor overpowers the rest of the salad.
I also add grated apple, kiwi, and sometimes grapes.
No need to use extra pudding/Tang/juice if you double or add to fruits.

title: fudge marble pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients except small packet in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour 3/4 of batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Blend contents of small packet into remaining batter; pour over first batter. Top with remaining batter
Pull knife through batter in wide curves.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until center springs back when touched lightly.

title: apricot treat
directions: Pour some nectar in sherbet cup.
Put a scoop of lime sherbet in.
Serve as dessert or cocktail before dinner.

title: walla walla onion pie(similar to a quiche)
directions: Saute onions in oil and butter until a light brown.
Combine eggs, flour, salt, pepper and spice.
Add about 1/2 cup of cheese. Lay the onions onto the partially baked pie crust and pour the egg mixture over them.
Sprinkle the rest of the cheese over the top and bake at 375° about 25 to 30 minutes until a golden brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until fork-tender.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion and saute until just tender, not brown.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Have cheese at room temperature and mix both until well blended.
Stir in garlic powder and pecans.
Form into a log about 10-inches long.
Spread chili powder on waxed paper and coat the outside of cheese with chili powder by rolling over the waxed paper.
"Chill."
Slice and serve with crackers or Melba toast.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat sugar and cooking oil.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt and add to the sugar, oil and eggs mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in the apples, coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: pat a pie crust
directions: Sift sugar, flour and salt together in pie plate.
With fork, in small bowl, whip together oil and milk.
Pour over flour mixture.
Mix with fork until all flour is damp.
Press against bottom and sides of pie plate.
Crimp edges.
Fill with fruit filling.
If want top crust, reserve 1/3 of dough, then crumble over top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, reduce to 350° for 45 minutes.
For shell only, 350° for 20 minutes.

title: knob hill sandwiches
directions: Combine and spread on hamburger bun.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender; drain.
Peel and cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, bacon, cheese and onions.
Combine mayonnaise, cream, mustard and pepper.
Add to potatoes.
Toss to coat.
Cover and chill for 6 to 24 hours.
Makes at least 12 side dish servings.
Enjoy!!!

title: sweet, sour and spicy pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
Discard juice.
Keep jar.
Slice pickles into 3/4 to 1-inch pieces.
Starting with sugar, alternate layers of sugar and pickles.
Sprinkle each layer with garlic and red pepper.
Store in refrigerator for 4 to 6 weeks.
Sugar will turn to juice making very crispy pickles.
More or less garlic and red pepper can be used according to individual taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook onion, potatoes and sliced bacon in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Add both cans of corn, soup, milk and seasonings. Continue to cook until heated through.
Serve topped with a little shredded cheese, if desired.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Mix water, sugar and Kool-Aid until dissolved. Put in gallon milk jugs in freezer.

title: beef goulash
directions: Cut beef in cubes; coat with flour to which salt and pepper have been added.
Brown, using shortening, in large pan (electric frypan works well).
Add sliced onions to meat until onions are limp, not browned.
Add small amount of soy sauce, bay leaf and enough water to cover beef.
Simmer covered until meat is tender, stirring occasionally and adding water as needed.

Mix flour and water to paste consistency; slowly stir into pan to thicken gravy. This is an excellent company dish, served with either mashed potatoes, noodles, rice or over bread slices if you are in a hurry. May be frozen.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool 10 minutes and serve hot or cold.
Enjoy.
Stays in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone.
Combine all ingredients including enough chicken broth to moisten to a good consistency (usually about 2 cups broth).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in 19 x 9-inch pan.

title: pineapple tart cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake as directed on the package.
Mix vanilla pudding and cream cheese and pour over the cooled cake.
Drain the pineapple and pour over the pudding mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Then place pecans on top of coconut.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° in a covered dish for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Pour small amount of oil into a 8 x 10 inch iron skillet and put in oven to heat.
Add corn, vegetable oil, eggs, sour cream, onion, green pepper, and jalapeno peppers to corn meal.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into hot skillet and bake for 30 - 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: rice flour muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine with liquid ingredients.
Do not overbeat.
Bake in oiled muffin pans at 425° for 20 minutes. Yield:

title: ham, muffin and cheese snacks
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Place approximately 2 ounces of ham and a slice of tomato on toasted muffin.
Mound 1/4 cup of rice on tomato and cover with slice of cheese.
Heat and melt cheese in broiler.
Serves 8.

title: turkey meat loaf(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, stir chicken bouillon into 1/2 cup salsa.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine turkey, oats, onion, basil, garlic powder, pepper and egg white.
Mix well.
Add bouillon mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into ungreased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan or shape mixture into an 8 x 4-inch loaf in ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes or until well browned and firm.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Heat 1 cup salsa in small saucepan until warm.
Serve with meat loaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Heat water; dissolve jello in it.
Whip cream cheese into jello.
Thicken slightly in refrigerator.
Beat in whipped cream.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube cake pan or Bundt pan.
Heat the milk, shortening and 1/4 cup of water until very warm, about 120°.
The shortening does not need to melt.
Blend 1 1/3 cups of flour with the sugar, salt and dry yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Blend the warm liquids into the flour mixture.
Beat with an electric mixer at medium speed for about 2 minutes, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally.
Gradually add 2/3 cup of the remaining flour and the eggs; beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Add the remaining flour; mix well.
The batter will be thick, but not stiff.
Cover; let the dough rise in a warm, draft-free place (about 85°) until it doubles in bulk, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: aunt frances' cheese cake
directions: Beat 3 eggs with sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour in graham cracker crust in spring-form pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with your favorite topping.

title: maple cream pudding
directions: Bring maple syrup and butter to a boil and simmer 10 minutes; let cool.
Place egg yolks in top of double boiler and beat slightly.
Add cooled maple syrup mixture, cornstarch, mixed with 1/4 cup of cream and salt.
Mix well, then gradually add the rest of the cream.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Stir often or cover to prevent skin from forming.
Stir in bitters.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into individual serving dishes.
Chill. Serve plain or with whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked french toast
directions: Baking dishes:
Use either 1 (9 x 13-inch) or 2 (8 x 8-inch) dishes.

title: corn-on-cob(microwave)
directions: Place all ingredients in large baking dish.
Cover with wax paper, or plastic wrap.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn corn over after 5 minutes and test for doneness.

title: cheese and vegetable casserole
directions: In buttered pan, alternate layers of spaghetti and vegetables. Place bread crumbs on top and bake 35 minutes.
Then cover with cheese and bake until melted at 350°.

title: orange skillet and squash boats
directions: In 350° oven, place squash, cut side up.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pour a little water (about 1/2-inch) in pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer on low heat about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and 2 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth. Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up. (At this point, dough can be refrigerated 3 to 4 days.)
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
(Dough is ready if impression remains when touched.)

title: johnny o'shea
directions: Cook noodles.
Butter a large casserole dish.
Brown and season hamburger.
Layer half noodles, half hamburger, half onions and peppers and half sauce.
Repeat layers holding sauce.
Push strips of cheese into mixture.
Add remaining sauce.
Cover with bacon strips.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: old-fashioned creamy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, baking chocolate, corn syrup and salt in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Cook, stirring occasionally to 234° or until small amount dropped into cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir. Allow fudge to cool at room temperature without stirring until it reaches 110°.
Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Pour quickly in greased pan, about 8-inch square.

title: clinton's chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt on wax paper or in a bowl.
In a large bowl, mix shortening, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture and rolled oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: chicken dumplings(my mama's recipe)
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Turn out on a well floured paper and knead the dough
until
you
can
handle it.
Divide dough into 4 balls and
roll
out thin; cut into small pieces.
Have chicken broth boiling to a full rolling boil as you drop dough pieces in. Do not
stir.
Take
a
fork
and lightly separate. Lower heat. Add
chicken,
which
has been deboned, and black pepper.
Cover and let
set
for
about
1 hour.
This makes a large pot of dumplings.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Sift together the remaining dry ingredients twice.
Mix dry ingredients well with creamed mixture.
Shape into balls and dip in sugar.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Let stand on cookie sheet until cooled.

title: pat's quick and easy lemon pie
directions: Mix milk, beaten egg yolks and lemon juice well. Pour into pie shell. Top with meringue made from egg whites. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: diabetic pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle arrowroot over concentrate apple juice in a small saucepan.
Over low heat, stir until clear and thickened.
Cool this.
Beat in eggs, butter, vanilla, lemon juice and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans and pour into a partially baked pie crust. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 300° and bake 20 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk according to directions on box.
Mix the pudding and Cool Whip.
Alternate one layer of vanilla wafers and one layer of bananas and smooth pudding mix until covered. Alternate layers until pudding is used up.
Refrigerate.

title: boiled crabs
directions: Bring water to a boil with cayenne pepper and salt.
Add crabs. Cover and bring to boil again.
When steam appears from the edge of the lid, cook for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy turkey and spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, cook turkey in oil until no longer pink. Drain Veg-All, reserving liquid. Combine liquid with soups and milk. Add soup mixture to spaghetti and mix with turkey, vegetables, mushrooms and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Spoon into 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Make 5 quarts popcorn.
Cook syrup until it threads.
Pour hot over popcorn.
Form into balls.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain.
Add beef to bacon grease and brown well.
Remove and place in bottom of deep casserole or Dutch oven.
Brown carrot and onion.
Add seasonings and flour.
Add bouillon and mix well.
Add this mixture to casserole.
Add bacon, tomato paste and onions.
Cover and cook at 325° in oven or medium-low stove top; heat for 2 1/2 hours (until beef is tender).
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons oleo and add to casserole, along with wine and cook 40 additional minutes.
Serve with noodles or rice.
If cooking in crock-pot, follow same layering directions and cook on low, 8 to 10 hours.

title: sticky bun cake
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter and pour in tube pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over butter.
Melt remaining 1 stick butter.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon in separate bowl.
Dip frozen balls in butter, then roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Lay in tube pan in one layer.
Cover with towel and let rise overnight or 8 hours on top of stove.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes. Turn over and dump out.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Sprinkle jello (dry) over softened Cool Whip and mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: Cook
or roast chicken until tender, roasting or baking gives richer flavor.
Remove meat from bones.
Chop and add to remaining ingredients.
Heat together, then
ladle
into jars. Process 60 minutes at 10 pounds pressure, or serve.

title: sunshine slaw
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pecans.
Work mixture into ball.
Roll in ground pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: amish cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, powdered sugar and oil.
Then add eggs and vanilla.
Cream well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten using the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Watch closely to prevent burning.

title: buckwheat pancakes
directions: Beat together egg yolks, honey, milk and butter or oil.
Sift together flours, salt and baking powder.
Stir egg yolk mixture into flour mixture.
Beat egg whites until they are stiff, shiny peaks.
Fold into batter.
Heat frying pan; spoon in batter.
Cook until bubbles and edges are browning.
Flip.

title: beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients, except potatoes, into a 3-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf and stir in potatoes.
Bake, covered, for additional 1 hour or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Yields 8 servings.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine Karo, water, salt and sugar.
Boil until a little tried in cold water is brittle.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually beat into the boiling syrup.
Whip until it begins to stiffen.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until it will barely pour. Pour in buttered pan.
When almost cool, cut in squares.

title: quick and tasty orange roughy
directions: Sprinkle onions and mushrooms over the bottom of an oblong glass dish.
Arrange fillets over vegetables, overlapping only the thin part of the fillets.
Season the fish with salt and pepper. Sprinkle the lemon juice over all.
Top with crushed croutons; pour butter over all.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, covered, and for 5 minutes more, uncovered.

title: s'mores
directions: For each S'more, place 4 squares of milk chocolate candy bar on a graham cracker.
Toast a marshmallow over charcoal grill or campfire.
Slit it into the chocolate and top with second graham cracker.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: You will need skewers.

title: ruby's ice cream dessert
directions: Brown almonds in butter.
Add brown sugar, Chex and coconut. Place half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with ice cream. Top with remaining mixture.
Freeze until serving time.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put chicken in 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour on top of chicken and bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Pour off fat.
Blend in pizza sauce, garlic salt, 1/2 teaspoon salt and oregano.
Put mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
In small bowl, mix eggs, milk, oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and flour.
Pour over mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
May also add before batter, mushrooms and bell peppers.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, water and raisins in saucepan. Add salt. Bring to a boil. Cover; remove from heat. Let stand until cool. Pour milk into bowl; add pudding mix and nutmeg. Mix according to directions on package. Stir in cooled rice mixture. Spoon into serving dishes. Chill at least 15 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: tucson black and white bian salsa
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet over high heat.
Add corn and saute until brown.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add 2 tablespoons oil and remaining ingredients.
Season generously with salt and pepper. Cover and chill.
Bring to room temperature before serving.
Can make 2 days ahead.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: breakfast omelet
directions: Fold all ingredients together and pour into medium hot buttered skillet.
I usually use a Teflon nonstick skillet. After pouring into pan, watch carefully, then fold over with spatula.
Serve with hot buttered toast or hot biscuits.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and heat to simmer.
Simmer until dark and thick.
Taste and add brown sugar, if too tart.
Takes about 1 hour.

title: alpine asparagus quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cook asparagus and drain.
Combine milk, cream, onion, salt, nutmeg and pepper in saucepan.
Bring to boil and simmer 1 minute.
Stir hot mixture into eggs.

title: cake icing
directions: *Add more milk for spreading on cake.

title: smoke on the mountain
directions: Mix flour, margarine and chopped pecans together.
Press into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350° or until brown. Cool.
Mix the powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup of Cool Whip together.
Spread over pastry.
Mix chocolate pudding with milk; spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip; refrigerate.
(Buy a bowl of Cool Whip and use according to recipe.)

title: shrimpies
directions: Combine all ingredients (except muffins) to make a spread. Cut muffins in half and spread with shrimp mixture.
Put in freezer for 6 to 8 minutes, then cut into quarters or desired size.
You may refreeze.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: grilled sliced tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes and sprinkle top of each half with the basic Italian coating of cheese, salt, pepper, oregano and basil to taste.
Pour drawn butter over each tomato half.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Run under broiler until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients, except walnuts.
Place in bowl, then top with nuts.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed beef rolls
directions: Soak bread in water and gently squeeze dry; add to ground sirloin.
Add in eggs, grated Parmesan and salt, pepper (to taste), nutmeg and parsley.
Mix thoroughly

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in beaten eggs, then in bread crumbs.
Brown in oil or in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour.
Arrange in baking dish and sprinkle with 6 ounces Mozzarella cheese and grated Parmesan cheese.
Pour spaghetti sauce over all and sprinkle with remaining 2 ounces of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for about 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Serve with your favorite pasta.

title: cindy's famous chicken wings
directions: Marinate overnight covered.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Cook uncovered.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning mix. Spread bean dip in bottom of serving dish, leaving room at edges for tortilla chips. Spread taco mixture over top of bean dip. Add tomatoes, olives and onions. Top with shredded cheese. Place tortilla chips along edges of serving dish. Serve with additional tortilla chips for scooping. Makes 25 servings.

title: aunt jane ashe's german slaw
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, vegetable oil, salt, pepper and celery seed, but do not boil.
Shred cabbage, green pepper and onion. Pour hot syrup over shredded vegetables.
Mix well.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: brodyinkle's kraut salad
directions: Combine the vinegar, sugar and celery seed and bring to a boil. Cool and pour over kraut mixture. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: strawberry shortcake(lo-cal)
directions: Beat two egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar and set aside.
Beat margarine, sugar, egg yolk and salt.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add baking powder to flour.
Add liquid and dry alternately as you mix.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Put in a greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until done and golden brown.

title: health salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add other ingredients.
Top with salad dressing mixed with cream.

title: country french baked chicken
directions: Place chicken, carrots, potatoes, onions, wine and broth in small roasting pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Roast, uncovered, at 400°, basting chicken and vegetables.
Cook bacon until browned, not crisp.
Add garlic and mushrooms.
Saute until mushrooms are lightly browned.
Add to roasting pan after chicken has cooked 30 minutes.
Roast for an additional 15 to 20 minutes. Remove chicken and vegetables to a platter; keep warm.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Use the flour and oil to make a roux.
Chop onion, celery, pepper and okra.
Put in pot with water to boil.
Add tomatoes; cook until done.
Put into blender until blended.
Add 1 gallon water to roux.
Add blended vegetables.
Stir well.
Bring to boil.
Add crab meat and crab boil.
Add peeled shrimp.
May use more shrimp if desired.
Cook until shrimp are done.
Add file. Serve with rice.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well. (Chill 5 minutes.) Whip the cream according to directions and fold into pudding mixture. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl. Top with vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding. Chill.

title: sweet potatoes with bourbon and walnuts
directions: Cut cooked potatoes in half and scoop out pulp (about 8 cups) into large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Let cream cheese get real soft first.
Serve with fruit.

title: sunrise cherry pie
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving two tablespoons syrup. Combine softened cream cheese, vanilla and reserved syrup, mixing until well blended.
Stir in 1/4 cup pineapple and 1/2 cup pie filling. Gradually add sugar to cream, beating until soft peaks form.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.
Top with remaining pineapple and pie filling.
Chill until firm.

title: white flour tortillas
directions: Sift the flour and then again with baking powder and salt. Cut in the margarine and slowly add water to make a pliable dough. Make 12 balls.
Cover with wax paper and let stand for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll out into circles on a floured surface.
Fry in an ungreased hot griddle.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with nuts and cherries.
Chill.

title: grandma ruth's silver bells
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut out shapes.
(Grandma Ruth made bells!)
Bake on ungreased baking sheet.
Cool.
May be frosted with thin icing.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Let cream cheese and margarine soften.
Add sugar and vanilla. Use mixer to blend all ingredients.
If frosting is too soft to spread, refrigerate a few minutes.

title: poor man's beef stroganoff
directions: In a large frying pan, put in the butter. Add mushrooms and saute 3 minutes.
Add some minced onions.
Saute some more until onions turn translucent yellow. Throw in hamburger and smash it all around until it turns dark grayish brown.
Drain off liquid. Add 1/2 cup sour cream and simmer while preparing rice or noodles. Put the rice or noodles on the plates.
Plop on the junk from the frying pan and add a blob of sour cream on top of it all.
Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix and heat for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel nut rolls
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients together.
Sprinkle some nuts on bottom of pan.
Pour half of syrup mixture over nuts and put biscuits on end so they touch each other.
Place rest of nuts and syrup over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Place the first four ingredients in a saucepan and barely bring to a boil.
Pour this over sugar, salt and flour.
Mix and add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: my grandmother's custard
directions: Put dry ingredients in pan.
Beat eggs separately.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add milk, stirring in a little at a time to avoid lumps.
Set pan in boiling water (double boiler).
Stir until it thickens.
Test on a wooden spoon.
Coats spoon when done.
Use a drop of yellow food coloring to add color and add vanilla.
Do not let it curd, but cook until it coats wooden spoon.

title: hot dog hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend sugar, ketchup and whiskey in heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens.
Cut franks into fourths.
Add to sauce and cook until hot.
It will take about 30 to 40 minutes for sauce to thicken, another 10 to 15 minutes for franks to cook.

title: cherry delights
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put small amount in palm of hand. Place cherry in center and roll into a ball.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Let stand a few hours.

title: very special shrimp dip
directions: Whip all together with an electric portable beater or hand beater until well mixed and smooth.
Chill before using.
Keeps for a week under refrigeration.

title: cooked chicken sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate rolls into 4 squares.
Mix remaining ingredients, except crumbs and butter.
Divide mixture evenly on middle of each dough square.
Roll dough around mixture; pinch edges.
Place on cookie sheet.
Put crumbs and butter on top of each roll.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: taco beef casserole
directions: In large frying pan, saute onion in oil; push to sides of the pan. Add ground chuck or sirloin and saute until brown, stirring. Add taco seasoning and water. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add corn. Reserve 1/3 cup olives for topping. Coarsely chop remainder and add to meat mixture.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Place cream cheese, cottage cheese and mayonnaise in bowl. Beat until blended, about 1 minute.
Scrape bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and combine.
Refrigerate until serving.
Serve with assorted crackers or raw vegetables.
Yields 3 cups.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes after mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from stove.
Quickly add oats, nuts, peanut butter and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Spoon out onto waxed paper into cookie size portions.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil 1 whole chicken until it is done; remove from broth and set aside to cool.
Measure 1 1/2 cups of broth.
Chop 1 large onion and cook in broth until tender.
Crush tortilla chips; add in large bowl to taco sauce, stewed tomatoes, soups, chicken broth with onion and the boned chicken and salt and pepper to taste. Add to casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: light dinner rolls
directions: Proof the yeast in the water and a little of the sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients except for 2 cups of flour.
Beat well. Add the remaining two cups of flour.
Mix until very smooth and velvety.
Scrape down the sides of the bowl, cover with a cloth and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.

title: marinade for pork tenderloins(this marinade is enough for 6 whole tenderloins.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate tenderloins for at least 24 hours, covered in refrigerator.
Preheat grill.
Cook on hot grill 6 minutes on each of four sides, total of 24 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl. Pour into cake pan. Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: p.o.t. casserole (potatoes, onions, tomatoes)
directions: In 2 or 3-quart casserole, either layer or mix potatoes and onion. As you layer, sprinkle with oregano, salt and parsley. Dot with margarine. Slice tomatoes thin. Place on top of potato and onion mixture. Cover with plastic wrap. Punch 1 hole in center of plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 20 minutes. Check for tenderness. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of tomatoes. Cover with plastic wrap. Let set 6 to 8 minutes before serving.

title: one-dish chicken and dressing
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions, omitting butter.
Spread in greased 10 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with chicken breasts.
Salt and pepper each breast and top each breast with a pat of butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and pour gravy on top.
Return to oven until hot, about 10 more minutes.

title: chewy monkey bars
directions: Heat first five ingredients together in a saucepan, stirring to blend.
In an 8 x 8-inch square pan, combine oats, rice cereal, coconut and peanuts.
Pour honey mixture over dry ingredients. Mix until thoroughly coated.
Pack mixture firmly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into 16 bars.

title: roasted onions
directions: Use flat plan like roasting pan or flat casserole dish.
Use medium yellow onions.
If there is soil on onions, wipe off gently. Do not take off skins.
Take 7 or 8 onions root ends off slightly so onions can stand up in pan.
Cut other ends a little.
Stand onions in pan in rows in one layer.

title: oyster-olive spread
directions: Finely chop oysters.
Combine with olives and just enough mayonnaise to bind them together.
Chill before serving.
Serve with your favorite crackers, rounds or chips.
Yields 1 cup.

title: low cholesterol meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth by hand.
Form into loaf and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Drain juices off as they form while baking.
Last fifteen minutes top with 1/2 cup mushroom spaghetti sauce.

title: egg-ham casserole
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bread, ham and cheese.
Add melted margarine.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon flour.
Beat eggs and milk. Add mustard.
Pour over bread, ham and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: molded salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Place over cut up marshmallows and let stand for 1 hour.
Mix together cream cheese and salad dressing; add to fruit.
Whip cream and fold into mixture.
Refrigerate to mold in 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: stir-fried ginger beef
directions: In a medium bowl, mix 1 tablespoon soy sauce, 1 teaspoon sesame oil, crushed garlic, sugar and crushed red pepper.
Stir in beef and marinate, covered, for 20 minutes at room temperature.

title: dick's roquefort dressing
directions: Cream softened cream cheese with milk, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Crumble Roquefort cheese into mixture and mix well. Chill.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 stick of margarine and 1 pound ground beef. Cook tomato sauce or Prego or Ragu, garlic power and sugar.
If too thick, may add a little water.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Mix 1 stick of margarine and sour cream.
Layer spaghetti and sauce. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on each layer.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: softasilk cake
directions: Beat eggs first.
Beat butter and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Add eggs.
Add milk and flour, one cup at a time.
Bake at 325°.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Cook sugar and milk until sugar is dissolved. Add flour, butter and peanut butter and cook until thick. Spread on your favorite cake.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Make graham cracker crust for bottom layer (using a pan or Pyrex baking dish about 8 x 13-inches).
Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk; spread over crust.
Sprinkle some chopped pecans on top. Spread on Dream Whip (make this layer as thick as possible). Spread cherry pie filling on top (I use Thank You brand). Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Place a layer of cabbage in the bottom of a large stockpot (or crock-pot). Next, add a layer of mushrooms, then onions and finally a layer of the kielbasa. Season. Repeat layering process, seasoning between each layer.
Cover with water. Place lid on the pot and cook until tender.

title: mandarin salad eleanor
directions: Drain gelatin in boiling water.
Cool and add frozen orange juice; stir to melt.
Chill until slightly syrupy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or similar size mold.

title: never fail buns
directions: Put shortening, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Scald milk and pour over mixture.
Cool to lukewarm.
Meanwhile, combine water and the yeast; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir and add to cooled milk mixture.
Stir in egg.
Add flour and stir until thoroughly combined.
Cover bowl with greased wax paper and cleaned tea towel; let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down; dust hands with flour and shape into buns.
Place on greased cookie sheet; let rise until almost doubled, 30 to 40 minutes. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix and put into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: meat loaf
directions: Pour over meat loaf.
Continue to bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours, basting occasionally.
This meat loaf has a slight barbecue taste.

title: sparkling strawberry beverage
directions: In covered blender, blend strawberries and undiluted lemonade concentrate until mixed well.
Pour mixture into chilled punch bowl.
Add sugar, ginger ale, club soda and ice cubes.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add orange slice before serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Mix ingredients together the length of time on
package directions.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°. Frost with Cool Whip or Fluffy Frosting.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Saturate party rye bread in melted butter and bake until crispy.
(Use a frying pan on top of the stove.)
Drain artichokes and cut each into 3 to 4 pieces.
Place 1 piece of artichoke on the toasted bread and sprinkle with Lawry's seasoned salt.
Place a dollop of Hellmann's mayonnaise on top of each one and sprinkle with lots of Parmesan cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Store in tightly sealed jar.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush cookies; mix with butter.
Save 1/2 cup for top.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together 6 ounces Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread on crumbs.
Mix 2 1/2 cups milk with pudding; pour over top.
Put remainder of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle remainder of cookies.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Rinse shrimp; crumple.
Put together and form a ball.
Pour shrimp sauce over the ball when ready to serve.

title: sweet-and-sour chicken
directions: Place carrots in 3 1/2 to 4-quart slow cooker. Top with chicken; sprinkle with red pepper. Cover and cook on low heat setting 6 to 7 hours or until juice of chicken is no longer pink when center of thickest pieces are cut. Drain and discard liquid from slow cooker. Top with pineapple and bell pepper mixture. Cover and cook on high heat setting 45 to 60 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serve with rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: raisin sauce
directions: To 1 cup water add sugar and bring to a boil.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Then bring to a boil again.
Add 1 teaspoon cornstarch, dissolved in a small amount of cold water. Stir until mixture thickens slightly.
Serve hot on ham.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Form into a ball. Refrigerate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl sift first 6 items.
Add apples, nuts, butter and eggs.
It will be thick.
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour or until top springs back.

title: pam duffey's red lobster rolls
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Mix butter and garlic salt.
Brush on rolls as soon as removed from oven.

title: donald's peanut butter delight
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in large mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Gradually add whipped topping and powdered sugar and continue beating until smooth.
Freeze overnight or for 8 hours.

title: janie's hummingbird cake
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients

large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring.
Do

Stir

pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Spoon batter into floured and greased tube pan (for uniced
cake)

Cool completely on racks or spoon batter into

Cool completely and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: tortellini salad (cold)
directions: Cook tortellini as directed.
Drain with cold water and cool. Add dressing, pepperoni, olives, onions and Parmesan cheese.
Mix thoroughly and chill 2 hours.
Serve cold with sandwiches as you would any salad.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Put in quantities that you desire.
Fold up in a square of heavy duty aluminum foil.
Place in hot coals for 15 minutes, turn and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix well the Jell-O and boiling water.
Stir in pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Pour in dish and chill until firm.

title: gladys' cranberry chicken
directions: Mix cranberries, soup mix and French dressing.
Put chicken into a 9 x 13-inch casserole and pour mixture over chicken pieces; marinate covered in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in marinade uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: self-rising rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream the sugar and butter in a very large container with cover.
Add egg and yeast.
Carefully stir in flour.
Mix well.
Put airtight lid on bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Do not stir.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in large kettle, bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: aunt johnnie's cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and beat 2 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients in with first and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cornmeal-fried fish
directions: You will need 1 plastic bag.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Cook beef and onion on medium heat until it loses its red color; spoon off excess fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spread meat in baking dish.
Cover with undiluted soup and top with single layer of Tater Tots.
Bake 45 minutes or until it is hot and bubbly in center.

title: rhubarb butter crunch
directions: Combine rhubarb, white sugar and 3 tablespoons flour.
Place in shallow 10 x 10-inch greased baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix with pastry blender.
Spoon over rhubarb mixture. Bake 40 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Cook
rice,
milk, salt, cinnamon and cloves for 1 hour in
a double boiler.
Stir occasionally.	Remove spices.	Add sugar, eggs
and	vanilla.
Pour	into
greased
casserole. Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crusty baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking dish, which has a cover. Mix crumbs, pepper and salt in shallow bowl. Dip potatoes in oil, then roll in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: bea grassl's oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Combine first eleven ingredients.
Add the flour, then the oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Chill thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoon and flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen.
Dough or cookies freeze well.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and 10x sugar.
Then add milk and pudding; mix thoroughly.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Crush Oreos.
Line flowerpot with foil.
Layer cookie crumbs, then pudding.
Repeat, ending with cookies on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add gummy worms.

title: just good
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight, then eat.
Good!

title: pumpkin ring cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: creamy coconut cake
directions: Cream
shortening,
butter
and
sugar	until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine	flour,	soda
and
salt;
add
to
creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk; beginning and ending with flour
mixture.
Beat
well
after
each
addition.
Stir	in vanilla
and coconut.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add cream of tartar and continue beating until egg whites are stiff but not dry.
Fold	egg
whites into batter.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and
floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green beans fermier
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare green beans as label directs; drain.
Place beans in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Meanwhile, in a 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, cook bacon and onion 10 minutes or until bacon is browned and onion is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour until blended.
Gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups water, bouillon and pepper; cook, stirring constantly until sauce is very thick.
Gently stir sauce with beans; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes or until mixture is hot and bubbly. Makes 8 servings.

title: amaretti orestano(italian macaroons)
directions: Blanch almonds and place in warm oven 5 minutes to dry completely.
Chop almonds very fine until a powder.
Add sugar and mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry and add to almonds and sugar.
Add almond extract and blend all together gently, but thoroughly.
Butter and flour a baking sheet and drop batter by spoonfuls.
Leave 1 inch between cookies.
Shape spoonfuls of batter into ovals.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Let stand 2 hours and bake at 375° for 5 minutes or until delicately brown in color.
Makes 14 cookies.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Make cornbread as directed on package and crumble.
Mix with all other ingredients and let set for 2 hours.

title: green tomato cake
directions: Mix sugar, salt, baking powder, soda, spices (all ground).
Mix oil, eggs, vanilla and tomatoes.
Rub nuts and raisins in flour lightly.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into Bundt pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cream oleo and cream cheese until smooth and sugar and vanilla and mix until smooth and ice the cake.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, flavor and flour.
Roll thin.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix and pat into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brownies will appear real soft but do not overcook.

title: dijon chicken stir-fry
directions: Pound chicken breast to flatten.
Cut into strips.
Mix together mustard, cornstarch and broth.
Set aside.
Heat wok or skillet on high.
Add oil.
Add chicken, peppers and onion. Stir-fry 1 minute.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add wine and bring to a simmer.
Add tomatoes, water and Italian seasoning.
Cook 1 minute.
Turn heat back to high.
Add mustard mixture, stirring until slightly thickened and chicken is cooked.
Season with salt and pepper if desired.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry-banana float
directions: Combine 1 cup milk, 1 cup ice cream, strawberries and bananas in container of an electric blender; process until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining 1 cup milk and orange juice; process until smooth.
Pour mixture into 5 (10 ounce) glasses and top with a scoop of strawberry ice cream.

title: pioneer stew
directions: Cook ground beef, onions, and green peppers until meat is browned and vegetables are tender. Drain off fat.
Drain and reserve liquids from corn, tomatoes, and kidney beans.

Add reserved liquids, chili powder, and salt to meat mixture. Simmer, uncovered, until liquid is reduced to half, about 20 min. stirring occasionally. Add vegetables simmer 10 min. Stir occasionally. Combine flour and water; stir into stew. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cheese, (shredded) until melted. Seves 6.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, mushroom soup and Carnation milk. Cook ground meat and drain. Add onion, peppers and celery. Cook a few minutes. Add to cheese. Leave on low heat, stirring often to keep it from sticking, until ready to serve.

title: pineapple chutney
directions: Peel pineapple; remove core.
Chop to the size you wish. Place in pot with remaining ingredients and cook at least 30 minutes or longer, if you want thicker chutney.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed and drain.
Add Veg-All, tuna or chicken, salt, pepper, onion, cheese and pickles.
Mix sour cream, salad dressing and lemon juice together.
Toss with macaroni mixture.
Chill 6 to 8 hours.

title: by guess and by gosh potato salad
directions: Mix well and let stand 1 or 2 hours before serving.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Mix can of relish with softened cream cheese (at room temperature).
Stir by hand until the relish is completely blended into the cream cheese.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use. Serve with chips.

title: lamb cake
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar. Add eggs.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes. Sift, measure and sift flour, salt, mace and baking powder together. Sift again. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture in 3 installments.
Beat 1 minute after each addition. Add lemon juice. Beat 1/2 minute.
Pour into bottom and face of lamb. Place on cookie sheet in oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Lift lid off.
Usually done at this point.

title: snowballs
directions: Work and mold into small balls; roll in powdered sugar.
Store in tightly closed container.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through. Use a handle of a wooden spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Place potatoes in a micro-safe dish and sprinkle with chives, parsley and melted butter.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, turning the potatoes after 5 minutes.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Microwave for another 4 to 6 minutes on High until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft. Sprinkle with salt.

title: cajun catfish ala "a"
directions: Cut catfish in half; butter both sides of each piece and season with Cajun seasoning.
Stack catfish with parsley in between and wrap securely.
Wrap again two more times so no leaking can occur.
Wire package to "A" manifold just tight enough to keep package from bounding off.

title: renya's dip for oranges
directions: Mix and serve with oranges.
Very good!

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain grease off.
Boil lasagna noodles until tender; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to beef.
Season to taste.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Use 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place noodles in bottom.
Cover with meat sauce.
Place another layer of noodles.
Repeat second step.
Repeat until you reach the top of the pan.
On last layer of noodles, sprinkle Cheddar and Mozzarella over top until covered.
Brown in oven at 350°.
It will be light brown when done.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Combine ingredients in crock-pot, except cocktail links.
Add the cocktail links.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or overnight. Add water or bourbon if sauce gets too thick.

title: barbecue frankfurters
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender.
Stir in next 6 ingredients, 1/2 cup of water and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Score franks diagonally at 1-inch intervals.
Add to sauce; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Serve over toasted buns. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in baking dish.

title: kathie's chocolate eclair cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

In saucepan, bring water and 1/2 cup butter to a boil until butter is melted. All at once, add flour and salt. Beat until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Spread mixture into parchment lined jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake for 35 minutes.
Prick bubbles with fork while hot. Cool completely.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix and pour over spinach salad mixed with bacon, hard-cooked eggs and mushrooms.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Slice the English muffins and put 1 teaspoon of Ragu sauce on the halves of muffins.
Then put a pinch of Mozzarella cheese on top of sauce.
Then put 4 pieces of pepperoni on top of cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serves 10 children.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Use large crystal or see through bowl, preferably with fairly straight sides.

title: butterscotch supreme
directions: Mix the flour and margarine.
Spread in a 10 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes, or until slightly browned. Cool.

title: delicious pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pink punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Dissolve strawberry drink mix in cold water.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add pineapple juice and jello.
Refrigerate.
Add 7-Up and sherbet just before serving.
Makes 35 servings.

title: fried okra salad
directions: Chop tomato, bell pepper, and onion in medium bite sizes. Set aside in bowl.
Mix cornmeal and flour thoroughly and put in plastic bag.
Drop okra in bag and shake until well coated.
Fry SLOWLY in hot grease until DONE and golden brown.
Toss with chopped vegetables and serve immediately.

title: fruit dip for pineapple
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Beat cream cheese and marshmallow cream until smooth.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and form into balls.
Cook in sauce and water until rice is tender.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients.
Work into flour until stiff, like regular biscuit dough.
Roll and cook until lite brown at 450°.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Prepare apples and cover with water with two Tbsp. of lemon juice and set aside.
Sift flour, soda and salt and set aside. Use a large bowl and beat oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold in drained apples and pecans.
Prepare a greased and floured tube pan and bake in 325° oven for 1-1/2 hours.

title: quick brown sauce
directions: Rub pan with 1/2 clove garlic.
Melt butter; stir in flour until blended.
Stir in bouillon and water; boil, stirring constantly.
Season to taste.

title: cream cheesecake
directions: Mix until creamy and smooth.
Grease a 9 inch pan, very well. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in tiny muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 2 dozen tiny biscuits.

title: frozen macaroon dessert
directions: Crumble cookies into small pieces.
Whip the cream until nearly stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Reserve 1/2 cup cookie crumbs and sprinkle remainder on bottom of spring-form pan.
Pour with cream over crumbs.
Spoon sherbets by spoonfuls over cream. Alternate colors to give marbled effect.
Smooth off top of mixture and sprinkle reserved cookie crumbs.
Place in freezer for at least 24 hours before serving.
To serve, remove from freezer for 5 minutes before slicing.
Serves 15.

title: green beans with honey cashew sauce
directions: In large skillet, saute cashews in butter over low heat until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add honey and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute longer.
Pour cashew sauce over beans and toss until coated; spoon into serving dish and serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cover steak with flour.
Brown	meat
in
fat
and then pour off all but 2 tablespoons.	Brown 1 heaping tablespoonful flour in grease and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly for 2 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put chicken thighs in large saucepan; cover with water.
Add all seasonings.
Bring to boil; continue boiling until meat begins to fall off bone.
Remove thighs from water; take meat off bone and discard skin and bone.
Continue boiling water until about 2 cups remain in saucepan.
Add rice and boned chicken.
Cover; simmer for about 20 minutes, until all water is absorbed.
Drain and add peas.

title: raspberry sorbet
directions: Puree
raspberries
in	food
processor
until	smooth. Press puree through sieve over a bowl.
Add sugar, lime juice and lime peel;
stir until sugar is dissolved.
Set aside.
In small
bowl, whip
egg whites until soft peaks form; fold egg whites into raspberry mixture.	Pour into metal bowl or baking pan.
Cover and
freeze until 1 inch of ice has formed around pan,
about 1 hour.
Re-whip the mixture; continue this freezing	and whipping procedure 3 times.	Allow mixture to freeze. To serve, scoop sorbet as you would ice cream.

title: cheese dip (hot)
directions: Heat in small crock-pot.
Can add peppers, if desired.

title: fish kedgree
directions: Heat butter in large saucepan.
Stir in flaked haddock, cooked rice, eggs, seasoning and curry powder.
Stir well.
Add parsley and stir in cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples, oranges and orange rind in grinder and use juice from it.
Then mix Jell-Os with water.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate until set.
Makes a very large bowl.

title: granny's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs, flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet, two inches apart. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes over 100 cookies.

title: losfeliz casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Meanwhile, brown meat in butter.
Add tomato sauce and cook 10 minutes.
Combine cream and cottage cheese, sour cream, green onions, pepper and melted butter.
In 4-quart casserole, spread half the noodles.
Cover with cheese mixture, then remaining noodles.
Top with meat mixture and cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups water.
Stir in orange juice and cool in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple. Mix thoroughly and congeal.

title: mushroom pepper steak
directions: Put soy sauce in bowl.
Dip pieces of steak in soy sauce, then roll in flour.
Brown steak in oil over medium heat.
Add green pepper and saute a few minutes.
Add water and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: hot parmesan puffs
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, grated onion, Parmesan and pepper.
Cut 2-inch bread rounds with cookie cutter and bake on cookie sheet in 300° oven for 5 minutes to harden.
Spread the cheese mixture generously on bread rounds.
Sprinkle with extra grated Parmesan cheese and a dash of paprika.
Then broil until puffy and golden on top.
Serve hot.
Makes about 30.

title: fettuccine with roasted garlic and chili
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wrap each head of garlic separately in aluminum foil.
Place the parcels on a rack in the center of the oven and bake for 45 minutes.
Remove the garlic heads from the oven and set aside to cool slightly so that they can be handled.

title: diet cabbage soup
directions: Cover with water and cook 10 minutes.
Turn on low heat and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Makes a large pot full.
Soup may be eaten at any time of day and as much as you want.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tuna and rice casserole
directions: Pour oil from tuna into a saucepan.
Add green pepper and cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in soup, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Add milk; heat.

title: taco-bean appetizer
directions: Layer in this order:
Jalapeno bean dip, avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper (all mixed in food processor), then sour cream, taco seasoning mix and mayo.
Sprinkle green onion on. Layer tomatoes, black olives and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for approximately 35 minutes (until filling is firm).

title: harvest cheesecake
directions: Combine ingredients, press into 9-inch spring form pan.
Bake at 350 for 10 min.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: jambalaya casserole
directions: Cook rice (both kinds) in 3 1/2 cups of liquid (broth from chicken), according to directions on Uncle Ben's box.
Saute sausage pieces and onion (no extra liquid needed) for about 10 minutes.
Mix together cooked rice, chicken pieces, sausage and onion mixture and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pour into a baking dish (9 x 13-inch suggested).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: granny's banana pudding
directions: Add sugar and flour together.
Stir in eggs, then milk.
Add vanilla.
Cook until thick and stir while on stove (about 14 minutes).
Alternate vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.

title: consomme rice
directions: In large skillet on top of stove, melt margarine.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Add rice and brown a little.
Add liquid, salt and parsley.
Place in covered casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check in 30 minutes for consistency.

title: jack's peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter, cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk. Add Cool Whip and blend again.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze 2 hours.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: light 'n fruity pie
directions: *Suggested Fruits:

One cup whole raspberries, blueberries, diced orange sections, strawberries or banana or 1 can (8 3/4 ounce) apricots, sliced peaches or fruit cocktail, drained and diced or 1 can (8 3/4 ounce) crushed pineapple, drained.

title: donna carr's sixty minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk and have shortening melted (I use cooking oil in place of shortening).
Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Let rise 15 minutes. Work down and let rise 15 minutes. Shape into rolls and let rise another 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: bishop's chocolate pie
directions: Take Hershey bars, milk and marshmallows and melt in double boiler or microwave.
When cool, add whipping cream, place in graham cracker crust, cool in refrigerator until firm.

title: meatballs(swedish)
directions: Mix well.
Make small balls and brown in oven at 400° for short time (or frying pan).
Mix gravy mix and onion soup mix according to package directions.
Add mushroom pieces.
When meatballs are browned, pour gravy mixture over them and continue baking at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 80.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Precook in microwave for 10 minutes.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix the following with hamburger mixture the veggies, rice, beef cubes, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer and enjoy.

title: microwave pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a circle in a round microwavable dish. Place on top of each pork chop, 1 teaspoon ketchup, 1 teaspoon brown sugar, 1 teaspoon lemon juice and onion slice.
Microwave, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: reese's hot chili
directions: Stir both meats, onion and garlic in heavy, large saucepan over medium heat until meat is no longer pink.
Mix in beer, then all remaining ingredients except masa.
Cover and simmer until chili is reduced to 12 cups, stirring occasionally, about 3 hours.
Degrease chili.
Stir dissolved masa into chili.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.
(Can be prepared 5 days ahead.)
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use on chicken or ribs. Marinate 1 to 3 hours at room temperature.

title: aunt grace's whole wheat bread
directions: Cream sugar,
salt
and shortening; pour hot water over and stir
until
blended
and
dissolved.
Cool.
Meanwhile, sprinkle yeast
over
warm water (sprinkle a little sugar over to make yeast foam more quickly).
Beat eggs, which have been at room temperature
for 30 or more minutes.
Blend all above ingredients together
and
add
flours, mixing well.
(More or less flour
may be needed; make a fairly stiff dough).
Knead lightly on floured board
4 or 5 minutes.
Put into a greased container, turning dough
once,
cover
and put in warm place free from draft.
Allow to rise until doubled in bulk.

title: candy cane oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter and vanilla until creamy.
Add sugar gradually until fluffy.
Add water.

title: walt's mom's bar-b-que sauce
directions: Saute onions, garlic, celery, and butter.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 hour uncovered.

title: winter punch
directions: Place cinnamon and cloves in cheesecloth and heat with Cranapple juice in large saucepan; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Remove spice bag.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add vodka and ginger ale.
Float block of ice.

title: bar-b-cups
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add sauce and brown sugar.
After beef is cooked, line ungreased muffin tin with biscuits.
Fill with meat mixture. Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix by hand.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake in a 375 degree oven until golden brown.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Beat ingredients 30 seconds.
Fill greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: cabbage skillet dinner
directions: Shred cabbage.
Put ground meat in skillet.
Stir cabbage and meat while the meat browns.
If you like onion, add with the cabbage.
When browned, add soup and milk.
Stir and simmer for a short time.
Serve over cornbread.

title: cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt margarine.
In bowl, combine eggs, milk, flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat well.
Add spinach and cheese and mix well.
Pour into pan, combining with margarine.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve warm.

title: southern oven-fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Place in non-metallic container and pour buttermilk over, turning pieces to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 425°. Coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with oil.
Arrange chicken on a rack over sink to drain excess buttermilk.
Combine bread crumbs and seasonings.
Roll chicken pieces in seasoned crumbs to coat evenly.
Arrange in single layer in oiled pan.
Bake in preheated oven 30 minutes.

title: pickle and bean salad
directions: Mix mayo with a little pickle juice added at the last minute. Mix all ingredients and serve on lettuce. Keep cold until ready to use.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Combine syrup and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Put on buttered cookie sheet.

title: weega's casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium-size bowl, mix eggs and potatoes together and set aside.
Spray bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan with Pam.
Place chicken in single layer; add veggies and onions on top of chicken.
Take potato mixture and drop by spoonfuls on top of that.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over all.
Bake for 30 minutes, until top browns.
Very good low-cholesterol recipe.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes until tender and drain.
Mash smooth. Add all ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Cool.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
May be used any time within 2 weeks.

title: red applesauce salad
directions: Place applesauce in small saucepan.
Heat over medium heat until bubbly hot.
Add jello; stir until jello is dissolved. Cool.
Stir in 7-Up.
Mix well.
Pour into mold; chill until set. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done, then add rice.
Let set 5 minutes. Add mushroom soup.
Put in a pan.
Put cheese on top.
Melt in microwave.

title: potato wedges
directions: Clean potatoes; scrub well.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise.
Then cut into even wedges, leaving skins.
Boil potato wedges for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain and pat dry. Spread wedges in single layer on lightly greased baking sheet. Sprinkle with oil, spices and herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are golden and cheeses are melted.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, creaming well.
Separate 2 eggs; leave 2 whole.
Add whole eggs to creamed mixture, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Then add yolks, beating smooth again.
(Save the 2 egg whites for the filling.)
Sift flour and sift again with baking powder.
Add to rest of batter mixture, alternating with milk, beating smooth each time.

title: nacho chicken
directions: In a baking dish, layer half of nacho chips.
On chips, layer 1/2 of the cream of chicken soup, if you prefer sprinkle 1/2 jalapenos.
Repeat process using up all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: stromboli
directions: *Riches frozen loaves work wonderfully.

title: mini cocktail meatballs
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Add ground beef; blend well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes, turning once.
Serve with wooden picks.

title: chuck roast au gratin
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Place in large baking pan or Dutch oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spoon off fat.
Arrange potatoes around roast.
Pour soup over top; cover and bake 2 hours or longer until meat and potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: microwave chili dip
directions: Combine chili and cheese in a 2-quart microwave casserole. Microwave for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Serve with crunchy vegetables or tortilla chips.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Grind tomatoes, cucumbers, onions and bell pepper.
Put in colander and let drain.
Dissolve gelatin in 3 tablespoons of juice from colander.
Mix all ingredients and make sandwiches.

title: tropical punch(100% nutrasweet)
directions: Mix punch with 2 quarts water.
Thaw lemonade just before mixing and add to punch mix.
Add amount of water called for (4 cans water to 1 can lemonade).
Will serve 60.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in refrigerator.

title: pecan honeys
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar together; boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over single layer of crackers placed on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: chocolate-chip pudding cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package. When pudding comes to a full boil, remove from heat. Add dry cake mix. Stir well and pour into a 9x13 lightly greased

pan. (Batter will be stiff). Spread mixture to cover pan and sprinkle chocolate chips liberally over top, along with peanut butter chips and nuts, if using. Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees. Cool and cut into squares. This may be served plain or with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix berries and sugar and let stand 1 hour (stir often).
Add to boiling water the Sure-Jell and boil 1 minute.
Pour over berries and stir until juice is clear and begins to thicken.
Put in jars and let stand 12 hours.
Seal and freeze.
Makes approximately 12 pints.

title: *brownies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add chocolate, which has melted and cooled, then add vanilla.
Add sifted flour and blend.
Add nuts and mix into batter well.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch sheet cake pan for 35 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let cool before cutting.
Makes 2 dozen 2 x 2-inch brownies.

title: creamed sweetbreads
directions: Rinse and soak the sweetbreads in cold water for 2 hours. Drain and remove any fat attached.

Put the sweetbreads, vegetables, herbs, salt and pepper in a saucepan with water to cover. Simmer gently for about 15 minutes until the sweetbreads are tender. Drain, reserving 1/2 pint of the cooking liquid.
Keep hot.
Put the butter, flour, milk and reserved stock in a saucepan.
Heat, whisking continuously, until the sauce thickens, boils and is smooth. Simmer for 1 to 2 minutes.
Season to taste and add the lemon juice.
Add the sweetbreads to the sauce and simmer gently for 5 to 10 minutes. Garnish with parsley and serve at once with new potatoes and a green vegetable.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Melt caramels with milk and butter over low heat.
Pour over partly cooked cake.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips over mix. Pour remaining cake batter over all and cook for 20 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: smoked fish and eggs
directions: Bone, skin and flake fish. Melt butter or oleo in saucepan. Blend in flour and salt. Add milk. Cook, stirring until smooth and thickened. Fold in eggs, fish and onions. Serve on buttered muffins or hot biscuits. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: quick macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water.
In a 1-quart casserole, layer half the macaroni add a little salt and pepper and milk and top with half the cheese.
Cover with rest of macaroni, add enough milk to almost cover it and top with rest of grated cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs (from 1 slice dry bread) and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: In a bowl dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of boiling water.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in cranberry sauce.
Spoon into 8-inch square pan.
Spoon sour cream in top and stir through to marble.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and cook slow for hours until all is tender.
Serve with sandwiches.
This soup was eaten a lot when our children were younger.
Love you Troy, Tom and Chris. Remember those days?

title: creamed salmon and peas
directions: Melt Crisco on medium heat, slowly add flour, mix slowly to form a paste.
Slowly pour in all of the milk mixing as adding. Turn down to low heat, uncovered until it becomes a bit thicker. Add salmon and drained peas.
Dish is ready when fully set.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and sift all dry ingredients.
Add chopped onion and egg. Pour boiling water over this mixture, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth.
Add more water, if necessary.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep hot fat.

title: chicken hoppin' john
directions: In large pan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove, drain and crumble and reserve.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons drippings from pan.
In same pan, place chicken and cook, turning until brown on all sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Adjust temperature to low.
Cover and simmer chicken for 15 minutes.
Add rice and onion to chicken in frypan.
Add chicken broth, hot sauce and stir.
Pour over chicken.
In bowl, mix black-eyed peas, parsley and thyme. Add to frypan.
Stir gently to mix.
Cover and cook about 25 minutes longer or until tender.
Sprinkle top with bacon and serve.

title: transparent pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add half and half and vanilla.
Put in unbaked pie crust and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes more at 350°.
Top with meringue and brown slightly at 350°.

title: linguini and clams
directions: Saute onion, then heat clam sauce and clams thoroughly.
Spoon over cooked linguini with a squeeze of lemon juice and top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Remix once a day for the first 3 days.
On the fourth day, shape into rolls.
Bake on broil rack oven pan to catch drippings.
Bake at 150° for 10 hours. Refrigerate after cooking.
Slice very thin.
Makes 6 rolls.

title: snowman buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, shortening, 2 eggs, nutmeg, salt and 2 cups flour.
Beat on low speed, scraping bowl constantly 30 seconds.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, beat egg yolks; add sweetened condensed milk and ReaLemon juice.
Pour into crust.
In mixing bowl, beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar; beat until stiff.
Spread on pie and seal to edge.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is brown.

title: french vanilla bars
directions: Shape in 9 x 13-inch pan as you would a pie crust.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool on wax paper before storing.

title: baked ham
directions: Rub ham with butter. Pack top with brown sugar. In a large bowl, combine all liquids evenly. Place ham in baking dish and pour liquid over it. Soak overnight or longer. Bake at 350° until ham is done. Reserve left over juice to store left over ham in. The longer it soaks, the better it is!

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Pour off all fat and debone chicken.
In a pot, combine chicken, water, bouillon and all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes.
Season to taste.
(I like Mrs. Dash table blend and/or extra spicy.)
Serves 3 to 5.

title: festive potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first seven ingredients.
In another bowl, combine the mayonnaise, sour cream, yogurt and seasonings.
Pour over potato mixture;
toss to coat.
Gently stir in tomatoes, peas and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: creamy baked chicken breast
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle oleo over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: carrot and orange salad with dill
directions: Working over a bowl, peel and cut the white membrane away from the orange.
Slice it into segments and set aside.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; add red pepper, salt and chili powder to taste, then add taco seasoning.
Let this cool.
Mix other ingredients together, then add tortilla chips just before serving. Serve with French dressing or whatever you prefer.
This makes a large amount.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed on package.
Spread in shallow 2-quart dish.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: italian chicken spaghetti
directions: Chop chicken into small bite-size pieces (it helps if chicken is slightly frozen).
In large Dutch oven add olive oil and chicken.
Fry until golden brown.
Add a little salt to the chicken, then add tomatoes, sugar and seasonings.
Mix well. Cover and simmer for 1 hour on medium-low heat.
Cook spaghetti in large stockpot according to box directions.
For best results when done cooking, run cold water in the pan to stop cooking action, then drain well.
Add spaghetti and sauce, small amounts at a time, back to stockpot and mix well.
Serve with cheese, salad and garlic bread.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Moisten dough with enough water to give dough right consistency for handling.
Pinch off small amount of dough and roll out but not thin.
Use favorite filling, putting small amount on dough.
Fold over and seal.
Prick top lightly and fry.
(Can be baked instead of fried.)

title: fruited yam souffle
directions: Beat yams in bowl until fluffy.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until browned (about 45 minutes).
Or microwave at High power for 6 minutes.
Turn and microwave 6 more minutes.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put 2 or 3 teaspoons in a cup with hot water.

title: widerhold homemade sausage
directions: Cut boned meat into small enough pieces to put through grinder.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Put all through grinder. This will help mix the seasonings more evenly.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Cut chicken into strips and fry in oil "stir-fry" style until all or most pink is gone.
Add sauce and chilies.
