Reduce heat and simmer about 15 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Cut cheese into slices and lay on top of chicken mixture.
Cover and let cheese melt. Spoon into flour tortillas and fold into burritos.
Sloppy but delicious!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan in oven.
Remove pan and layer in order:
graham crackers, coconut, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook lasagne in boiling water, drain.
Place on layer of lasagne noodles in bottom of pan, cover with 1/3 of cheese mixture.
Place another layer of noodles on top of cheese.
Cover with your favorite spaghetti sauce.
Repeat layers of cheese and noodles.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 4 large baking sheets. Combine flour, ground ginger, baking soda, ground cinnamon, ground cloves, and salt in large bowl; mix well.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage and set aside.
Thaw bread dough.
Roll each loaf out in rectangular form and coat with melted butter.
Cover dough with a layer of sausage, olives and cheese.
Sprinkle with peppers and Parmesan cheese.
Fold sides up and ends over (jelly roll style) and seal bread.
Bake on greased pan at 300° for 45 minutes to one hour or until brown.
Makes three large loaves. They can be refrigerated or frozen until needed.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes; cut in half and scoop out.
Mash centers with the remaining ingredients.
Pile filling into potato shells. Heat for 10 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: caramel turtle cake
directions: Melt margarine, caramels and milk together; set aside.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour the caramel mixture over the top.
Spread chocolate chips and nuts over the top of caramel mixture.
Pour the other 1/2 of the batter over the top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 250°, then for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot.
Mix ingredients and pour over cabbage.

title: sand cups
directions: You also need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) clear plastic cups.

title: captains chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and fry quickly in butter or olive oil with a little butter, until golden brown. Remove from pan.
Add onions and peppers to remaining butter and fry until glossy.
Mix remaining ingredients into undrained tomatoes.
Add this to onion mixture.
Cook slowly 5 minutes. Arrange chicken in a 3-quart baking dish, pour the sauce over it and refrigerate or freeze until needed.
Bake at 350° covered for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with wild rice or brown rice.
Serves 8.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Put the margarine in a deep Pyrex dish.
Place in oven to melt.
Beat together the sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over the melted margarine (do not stir).
Pour the fruit over the batter. Sprinkle with the sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
(Batter will rise to the top.)

title: easy fried potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and pat dry with paper towel.
Microwave potatoes for 5 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Combine the beef, onion, green pepper and garlic in a 3 1/2-quart microwavable casserole.
Microwave uncovered on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain off and discard the fat.
Add the macaroni, water, pizza sauce and the mushrooms.
Cut the pepperoni slices in half and add them to the casserole.
Stir to combine ingredients and microwave, covered, on High for 15 to 18 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese over the casserole.
Cover and allow to stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat soup (do not dilute) and Ro-Tel tomatoes in pot.
In 1 1/2-quart baking dish, alternate layers of Doritos, onion, chicken and cheese. Pour soup mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry hill
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle blueberries with lemon juice. Combine sugar and flour and toss with blueberries, coating.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch baking dish.
Combine oats, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Sprinkle over berries.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream. Serves 6.

title: cherry delight
directions: Prepare Dream Whip per package directions.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar; mix well.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and 6 tablespoons melted margarine together and mix with crushed graham crackers.
Place in bottom of 9 x 9-inch dish.
Press lightly. Pour Dream Whip mixture on top of graham cracker crust.
Spoon cherry pie filling on top.
Chill for 4 to 6 hours before serving. Best if made the night before.

title: basic muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add liquid ingredients all at once to flour mixture and fold only until mixed.
Batter will be lumpy.
Place in greased muffin tins.
Fill to top (overflowing).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 large muffins.

title: williamsburg fondant
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and milk to make a dough.
Amount of milk may be increased to get a soft dough.
In a double boiler, mix small amount of paraffin and bakers chocolate and melt over a low heat.
Make small pieces of candy with the dough and using a toothpick, dip into liquid chocolate mix.
With a little practice you will arrive at the proper chocolate-paraffin mix to coat the candy and candy surface will be very glossy.
Immediately top with a pecan half.

title: campfire biscuits
directions: Pour oil in a shallow frypan.
Allow oil to reach medium to high heat.
Flatten biscuits out as thin as desired.
Lower into oil.
When sides appear to be browning, flip over.
Cooking time depends on temperature of oil.
Remove when golden brown and add personal flavor.
Biscuits may also be rolled into small balls and deep fried.

title: eggless chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together except flavor and cook in double boiler until thick. Then add flavor. Pour in baked shell.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and thickened.
Cool completely.
Fold in whipped cream.
Serve with fresh fruit.
(I sometimes omit the whipping cream.)
Yields 2 cups.

title: teriyaki shrimp
directions: You will need an aluminum throw-away pan.
Put teriyaki, butter, garlic and pepper in pan; set aside.
Peel uncooked shrimp. Place in separate bowl.
Place pan on grill at medium to medium-high heat.
When butter has melted, place shrimp in pan, turning at all times.
When shrimp is evenly pink on both sides, and still tender remove from heat.
Ready to serve.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add lemon extract and wine or fruit juice.
Combine flour and soda.
Coat fruit and pecans with flour mixture; add butter and sugar mixture.
Add six egg whites, which have been stiffly beaten.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours. Makes 3 loaf pans.

title: peanut raisin logs
directions: Mix peanut butter, corn syrup, milk and sugar.
Add raisins and mix well.
Chill candy mixture.
Divide into 24 pieces, forming each into a small log.
Wrap individually in clear plastic wrap.
Keep refrigerated.

title: florida key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and egg yolks.
Mix at low speed of mixer. Slowly add juice, mixing well.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: heavenly chili
directions: Add Accent and meat tenderizer to ground chuck.
Brown meat and drain fat.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and kidney beans.
Add brown sugar, chili powder, salt and pepper; mix well.
Cook on medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: classic creamed corn au gratin
directions: Combine corn, cream, salt, sugar and white pepper in a pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Make roux from butter and flour.
Add to corn.
Mix and remove from heat.
Transfer corn mixture to casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan
cheese and brown under broiler.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer 8 slices of bread in large casserole baking dish.
Add 1/2 of sausage and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Mix eggs, dry mustard and milk.
Pour over layers in casserole.
Whirl crusts in blender, then mix with 1 stick of butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Measure first 5 ingredients into a saucepan and bring to a full rolling boil (one which cannot be stirred down).
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Add oatmeal quickly; mix thoroughly.
Then drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Work as quickly as possible.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in broth.
Strain and save broth.
Melt oleo in saucepan, add onions, celery, and cook until tender.
Blend in flour and salt.
When mixture starts to boil add broth, milk, and soup and boil one minute.
In 9 x 13 baking dish layer noodles and sauce then top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: busy day pie
directions: * If you use plain flour, add 1 1/2 teaspoons baking powder and a pinch of salt.

title: roast duckling with normandy sauce
directions: Sprinkle duckling body cavity with salt.
Place duckling, breast side up, on rack in shallow baking pan.
Prick skin all over with sharp fork or knife; truss.
Roast in preheated 350° oven about forty minutes per pound or until duckling is tender and a deep brown.
Baste with Normandy Sauce last 30 minutes of roasting time.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: party dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with sour cream, milk, green pepper and onion.
Chop beef in small pieces and add to mixture. Place in an 8-inch baking dish.
Saute pecans in margarine and sprinkle on top of dip in baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes or until it bubbles.
Serve hot on crackers.
This can be mixed ahead of time and baked at the last minute.

title: applesauce donuts
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients, except nuts. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Set in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Take out and stir down.
Add additional flour if needed.
Cut with donut cutter and fry in hot grease at 375°.
Brown on one side until brown and turn.
(Can drop by teaspoonfuls, if you wish.)

title: beefy rice
directions: Brown hamburger and cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions on box.
Mix rice and hamburger together in microwave-safe bowl. Microwave 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve.
Kids really like it.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients with electric mixer. Beat in remaining ingredients and pour into 12 x 18-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine pumpkin, eggs, sugars, milk and cinnamon and pour onto cake mix in pan.
Mix reserved cake mix, oleo, sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cook the raisins until tender.
Drain. Save 1/2 cup water to dissolve the soda. Cream the sugar, butter or margarine and eggs. Add the oatmeal, liquid with soda and flour.
Drop with teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: noodle doodles
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in top of double boiler until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in chow mein noodles coating completely.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and chill.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix pineapple and cheese.
Mix sugar and flour and add to pineapple.
Place in casserole dish and cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour margarine over Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If too dry, use 6 tablespoons pineapple juice.

title: relyenong manok(stuffed chicken filipino style)
directions: Carefully take out bone and meat of whole chicken without tearing the skin.
Marinate chicken skin with soy sauce and lemon. Grind or chop chicken meat.
Mix ground pork, sliced vienna sausage, cheese, pickles, scrambled egg, soy sauce, dash of salt and pepper.
Mix ingredients well; tightly stuff chicken skin so that boiled egg should be in the middle.
Close tightly the opening of stuffed chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Saut onions in butter in a heavy saucepan until tender.
Add meat and brown on all sides.
Add flour, salt, pepper, herbs and garlic juice.
Stir until smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups bouillon and 1/2 cup wine.
Simmer 3 hours.
Add mushrooms.
Cook 1 hour more; add remaining bouillon and wine as needed.

title: soleil de dunkerque(sun of dunkirk)
directions: In a ceramic pan, take the juice of the pineapple, eggs and cornstarch.
Heat slowly and stir constantly for about 5 minutes, or until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat the cream with a mixer until light and fluffy.
Cut the pineapple into pieces.
When cooked mixture is cool,
mix with the pineapple and cream.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve cold.
Bon Appetit!

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Beat potatoes; mix with rest of ingredients and put into greased casserole dish.
Cover with topping and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Add onion, bay leaves and chopped celery to the tomato juice. Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and strain.
Add vinegar, lemon juice and sugar; chill.
Serve in small glasses.

title: old fashion macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as directed by manufacturer. Place half the macaroni in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half the onion, salt, pepper and cheese.
Repeat.
Pour Thin White Sauce over casserole.
Dot with butter.
Cover; bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: wild mushroom stuffing(12 servings)
directions: Place dried mushrooms in bowl.
Add 3 cups boiling water. Soak 30 minutes.
Drain; reserve liquid.
Squeeze mushrooms to remove excess liquid.
Cut out stems.
Slice mushrooms.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Spread butter on cookie sheet.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Place in a large bowl.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix together soups and milk. Pour over chicken in dish.
Top with stuffing mix.
Mix 1 3/4 cups chicken broth and 1 stick margarine (melted) and pour over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mary todd lincoln's almond cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine and beat together sugar, butter and vanilla until light and fluffy. Combine flour and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Stir in chopped almonds. Fold in egg whites. Pour in 2 greased and lightly floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans. Cool on wire rack. Fill and frost with white frosting. Garnish with fresh raspberries and almonds.

title: pickled banana peppers
directions: Let boil; drop in peppers and get them hot.
Pour in jars and add 1/2 teaspoon salt to each pint.

title: miniature red cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into small balls. Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: *If you want it creamy, mix with 1 cup of milk.
Cover bottom of baking dish with strips of bacon.
Add uncooked Minute rice over bacon.
Cover rice with chicken.
Mix soup and milk in separate bowl, then pour over everything in the dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tortillas (flour)
directions: Cut shortening in flour and salt.
Add water, enough to make a soft but not sticky dough.
Make into 18 balls.
Set aside about 30 minutes.
Roll out about 1/8-inch thick.
Bake on hot griddle. Serve warm with beans or chile con carne.

title: country meat loaf
directions: Put ground beef in medium bowl.
Add chopped onion and green pepper, salt, pepper, crumbled up crackers and eggs.
Stir with fork until well mixed.
Place in medium baking pan.
Press evenly to edges (flat on top).
Spread ketchup evenly over top.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all together real good, pour into uncooked pastry shell. Heat oven at 450° for 5 minutes. Turn oven down to 375° and bake pie for 15 minutes. Turn oven to 350° and bake 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Mix orange juice and lemon pudding and let set. Pour over fruit and refrigerate.

title: really different raisin pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat eggs and vanilla with sugar and butter mixture.
Blend together with raisins and nuts, then crumble pie crust mix and blend in raisin mixture.
Place in 9-inch pie plate and bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix oleo, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Mix well.	Form into balls.
Chill for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler, stirring constantly.
Insert toothpick in peanut butter balls and dip in chocolate.
Leave some peanut butter showing, so it will look like a buckeye.
Cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: *If you wish you may substitute sauce with 1 cup milk.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Crush Doritos in bottom of lightly greased casserole dish. Add layer of chicken.
Mix soups with milk and heat on low.
Pour soups over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Add cheese during last 5 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mash graham crackers into crumbs. Mix pudding mix and milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Make a layer of graham cracker crumbs and then a layer of pudding mix until all used up.

title: easy cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
Blend soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Melt oleo and mix with crumbs.
Top over broccoli and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix sugar, oil and eggs until blended; beat 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except apples and nuts.
Beat 1 minute. Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes. Let cool and top with vanilla glaze.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese and diced vegetables.
Chill and serve.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in ungreased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth. Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/2 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter; do not stir.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: dream frosting
directions: Pour milk into a deep, narrow bottom mixer bowl.
Add whipped topping mix and pudding mix; beat at low speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Gradually increase beating speed to high and whip until mixture will form soft peaks, 4 to 6 minutes.
Makes about 3 cups or enough to frost tops and sides of a two-layer or a 13 x 9-inch cake.
Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook first six ingredients until thickened.
Cool until warm. Slice bananas lengthwise; spread with peanut butter.
Pour sauce over them and serve chilled.

title: candy canes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Beat in egg and extract.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Spoon half of dough into another bowl and tint pink.
Pinch off a teaspoon of each dough.
Roll each into pencil thin strips about 5 inches long. Place side by side and pinch ends together.
Twist and place
on ungreased cookie sheets, bending into cane shape.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.

title: secret potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl beat together butter, 1/3 cup sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour, beating until blended.
Stir in potato chips and nuts.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on baking sheet.
Flatten cookies with bottom of glass dipped in additional sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
While cookies are still slightly warm, sift confectioners sugar over their tops.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain corn, beans and peas. Chop celery, onion and pepper. Combine vegetables. Heat sugar, vinegar and oil until sugar dissolves. Cool; pour over vegetables. Keep in refrigerator - will keep for a week.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add lard.
Blend together; last, add beaten egg and milk.
Don't stir more than to moisten.

title: veal casserole
directions: Remove any fat or gristle from cutlets and cut them into 1 1/2 to 2-inch pieces.
Dust with flour, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish and pour soup over top.
Add sherry or Worcestershire sauce, if desired.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for about 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: divine apricots
directions: Grease a 1-quart casserole dish with margarine.
Place apricot halves, cut sides up, in bottom of casserole.
Generously sprinkle brown sugar over apricots.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over brown sugar.
Dot with margarine.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger casserole(crock-pot meal)
directions: Place layers of the vegetables in the order given in crock-pot. Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Put the lightly browned ground beef on top of the celery.
Mix the tomato soup with the water and pour into crock-pot.
Cover and set to low for 6 to 8 hours.
(High:
2 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.)

title: biscuit dough
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Stir in corn oil.
Add milk and mix well.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: meringue for pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until they peak.
Place on top of pie.

title: mama green's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa.
Add a little cold milk to mix.
Scald or warm remainder of milk and pour into sugar mixture and cook until thick.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks through strainer and cook several minutes.
Add butter, then vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and add whipped egg whites to top.
Brown in 375° oven until peaks are toasted.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Place in a wide kettle alternate layers of sugar and berries. Bring slowly to a boil.
After the whole mass is boiling, cook 9 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the lemon juice or cream of tartar.
Let stand overnight.
The second day, boil for 9 minutes. Allow to cool; place in sterilized jars.
Seal with paraffin. Cooked this way, the preserves are beautiful and tender.
Jelly surrounds the plump, bright berries.

title: sausage and vegetable bake
directions: Pour 1/2 of water into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Prick sausage in several places and cut apart.
Evenly distribute sausage in pan.
Surround with potatoes, peppers and onion.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: yellow pound cake
directions: Whip cream to soft peaks and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add flour, salt and flavorings and mix well.
Fold in whipped cream with a rubber spatula.
Pour mixture into greased and floured stem pan or Bundt pan.

title: amy's pizza
directions: Place muffins faced up on a cookie sheet.
Spread sauce on each muffin and then sprinkle cheese on top.
Broil at 500° for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Heat fat or oil (3 to 4-inches) to 375° in deep fat fryer or kettle.
Measure 1 1/2 cups flour and remaining ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour.
Turn dough onto well floured cloth covered board; roll around lightly to coat with flour.
Gently roll dough 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
With wide spatula, slide doughnuts into hot fat.
Turn doughnuts as they rise to surface.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Carefully remove from fat.
Drain.
Serve plain, sugared or glazed.
Makes 2 dozen doughnuts.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough according to directions on package.
Arrange slices on bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Press dough evenly into pan to form crust.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely!!!

title: conch stew
directions: Fry out fat pork in a large pot.
Add water, cooking oil, salt, pepper and conchs.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes and cornmeal dumplings; cook 1 hour more.
If not tender, during last hour of cooking, add 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place egg whites in large bowl.
Beat with spoon until slightly frothy.
Add vanilla and Puritan oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 22 to 26 minutes.
Avoid overbaking.
Cool completely before cutting.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen brownies.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, water and oleo to make syrup. Simmer while preparing rest of recipe.

Peel and slice apples. Cream shortening into the flour and add the other ingredients. Divide the dough in 6 parts, roll each out, put apples in center, sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar and fold dough around the apples, sealing them.
Place the 6 in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the syrup over the dumplings and bake at 370° for 35 minutes.
Will serve 12.
Very rich, very good.

title: chili recipe no. 1
directions: Brown meat with potato and onion for about 20 minutes; strain it and then add water until level with meat.
Add the sauce, salt and pepper to taste and chili powder, then stir.
Add cornmeal mixed with a little water and beans.
Stir and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour to let flavors cook together!

title: jello pound cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients for 5 minutes at medium speed. Pour the batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Frost, if desired, or serve with fruit.
This cake is delicious as is.

title: bisquick raspberry swirl
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix Bisquick, sugar and butter until crumbly.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and lemon extract and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time and continue beating after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add alternating to creamed mixture with milk.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until cake tests done.

title: steak and potato pie
directions: Cut stew meat and potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Remove all connective tissue and fat.
Roll meat in flour that is seasoned with salt and pepper.
Cover with boiling water and cook in oven at 300° for 2 to 3 hours until tender.
Add bouillon and stir.
Allow to cool.
Add potatoes.
Put 1-inch rim of pastry on top of casserole dish.
Add meat mixture.
Make hole for pie bird in pastry top and place over casserole.
Moisten edges of pastry so they will stick together and make favorite fancy pie crust edges. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar. Beat and set aside.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar with Crisco and vanilla and beat.
Add egg yolks; beat until creamy.
Sift 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in egg whites and blueberries that have been floured.
Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan for 50 minutes (grease and flour pan).
Bake at 350°.

title: vanilla pudding cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and butter in 15 x 9-inch pan. Spread evenly on bottom.
Arrange pineapple on bottom.
Beat cream cheese until smooth; add to milk and pudding.
Spread.
Spread on bananas, then remainder of pineapple on bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: duck(tame and wild)
directions: Tame ducks are prepared the same as young geese for the table, that is stuffed with bread, butter, onions and pepper or with mashed and seasoned Irish potatoes.
Wild ducks should have fat claws small and supple the hen is more delicate.
Do not scald wild duck but pick them clean and singe over a blaze.
Draw and wipe well inside with cloth.
Rub inside and out with salt and pepper.
Stuff each duck with bread and butter stuffing.

title: 3-step cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Blend in eggs.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into pie crust.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup chips over batter.
Use no spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool for best results and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: beef a la mode
directions: Rub salt and pepper into beef.
Stick cloves around sides of meat.
Place in roaster.
Pour over tomatoes and onions; sprinkle in the browned flour.
Fill roaster about 1/2 full of boiling water.
Cook in 300° oven for 5 hours, basting occasionally. Cheaper cuts of beef may be used and it is just as good.
The gravy is wonderful on mashed potatoes.
Can be cut down to family size.

title: lucille's brown sugar pie
directions: Beat well the eggs.
Add the sugar, salt, vanilla and butter and beat until smooth.
Add the cream.
Stir until mixture is well blended.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes, until firm.

title: cinnamon-nut coffee cake
directions: Beat cake mix, vanilla pudding, butterscotch pudding, eggs, oil and water for 10 minutes.
Pour 1/2 batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Mix 1/2 of second mixture through batter with a knife.
Pour remaining batter over top. Swirl rest of second mixture through batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: jean's meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, eggs, milk and seasonings together well.
Add enough cracker crumbs for meat to be shaped into 2 loaves.
Place in roaster.
Score on top and place a strip of bacon on top.
Pour catsup around the meat.
Pour on another 1 to 1 1/2 cups of milk. Bake at 325° to 350° for 3 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soup, broth and drained peas and carrots.
Mix flour, baking powder, buttermilk and butter; spread on top of first mixture.
Place ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Heat fruit, water and 1/3 cup sugar until it comes to a boil. Mix 3/4 cup sugar, flour, baking soda, salt and milk.
Melt butter in a flat baking dish (rather deep).
Pour in hot fruit mixture, then pour in batter on top.
Cook about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and sour cream.
Add grated chocolate bar.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in greased tube pan.

title: garlic and rosemary roast chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pat chicken dry.
Sprinkle inside and out with salt and pepper.
Rub inside and out with flattened garlic and rosemary and place inside with lemon quarter.
Truss and sprinkle with paprika.
Melt butter with oil in heavy ovenproof skillet over high heat.
Add chicken, breast up.
Add shallots and 2 whole garlic cloves.
Cook until bottom of chicken is brown; stir vegetables frequently, about 4 minutes.
Add lemon juice and baste chicken with pan juices.
Sprinkle vegetables with rosemary.
Put skillet in oven and roast 45 minutes, basting chicken and stirring vegetables occasionally.
Mix bell peppers into skillet and cook 35 minutes until done.
Take shallots and peppers out as they get done.
Serve chicken warm or at room temperature.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix flour, sugar and beer together.
Spoon into greased loaf pan. Bake 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese and rice dish
directions: Cook rice and broccoli.
Melt Cheez Whiz either in microwave or in pan with boiling water on stove.
Mix all ingredients; put in a medium size bowl.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni magic casserole
directions: Add 1 tablespoon salt to rapidly boiling water.
Gradually add macaroni so that water continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally until tender; drain.
Combine macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Mix well; turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake in 375° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp risotto(serves 6)
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in rice to coat.
Add broth and bay leaf.
Cook rice.
Separately melt 2 tablespoons of butter; saute shrimp and garlic.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add shrimp mixture to cooked rice.
Add remainder of ingredients. Stir and serve.

title: eggplant in tomato sauce
directions: Slice eggplants.
Wash slices and sprinkle with salt.
Let sit aside.
Later, squeeze water out of eggplant and brown lightly in olive oil.
Set aside.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Line a 10-inch quiche dish or 9-inch pie plate with pastry. Prick holes in bottom and corners of pastry with fork.
Bake in a 450° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Layer half the broccoli over Parmesan cheese.
Continue with layers of half Swiss cheese and scallions.
Repeat with remaining broccoli, Swiss cheese and scallions.
Beat eggs.
Add chicken broth, cream, salt and Tabasco; mix well.
Pour over broccoli mixture in pastry shell. Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer, or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix rhubarb with the beaten egg yolks.
Blend in the sugar, flour, salt, nutmeg and melted butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in a pastry lined pan.
Bake in hot oven (425° or 450°) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325° and bake for about 35 minutes or until filling is firm.
Serve plain or with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients.
Add nuts.
Chill overnight. Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Use powdered sugar to dip your hands into as you roll balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler over low heat.
Dip balls into this mixture, one piece at a time, holding each with a toothpick.
Drop on waxed paper.
This candy is moist inside and has a hard coating of chocolate.
It stays fresh several weeks in a tight container. Makes 75 servings.

title: snow peas with sesame
directions: Place pea pods and carrots in a strainer.
Set the strainer in a sink.
Pour boiling water over vegetables for about 1 minute, then pat dry.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten breasts between 2 sheets of waxed paper to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place 1/2 slice of cheese and 1/2 slice of ham in center.
Roll up lengthwise, tucking edges inside.
Secure with wooden pick.
Combine next 3 ingredients; set aside.

title: summer relish(thunder and lightening)
directions: Mix vegetables together.
Pour a solution of vinegar, water and sugar over vegetables and mix together.

title: squash-tomato combo
directions: Cut squash in 1/2 and remove seeds.
Place cut side down in lightly greased baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes. Meanwhile in 10-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Cook onion and pepper in drippings until tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, sugar, salt, basil and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Remove squash from shells, leaving about 1/4-inch.
Cube squash and add to tomato mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon mixture into shells and garnish with bacon.
Great reheated. Serves 4.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator for 12 hours.

title: banana-honey muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches.
Prepare Streusel.
Reserve.

Mix bananas, milk, honey, oil and egg in a large bowl. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt just until flour is moistened. Stir in cereal. Fill each muffin cup about 2/3 full. Sprinkle Streusel evenly over tops. Bake about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers as directed on box and let cool.
Crumble one layer in bottom of bowl.
Spread half pudding mixture that has been made according to package instructions on top.
Put on half can of pineapple, 1 can pie filling, half Cool Whip and half pecans and cherries.
Repeat the process and chill.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix cherry pie filling, pineapple (drained) and Eagle Brand milk.
Add large Cool Whip and nuts.
If the color is not pink enough, add a touch of red food coloring.
Refrigerate.

title: 1-2-3 cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Good without frosting.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix pumpkin and oil.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into greased cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Tastes good with powdered sugar sprinkled on top or cream cheese frosting.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients until jello is well dissolved. Add raspberries.
Refrigerate until thick.
Fold in whipped cream and refrigerate.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Slice onions and break into pieces.
Cut broccoli into small flowerets and also cauliflower.
Toss this in a large container. In a small container mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar until well blended.
Then add small package of Ranch dressing; mix well.
Pour over vegetable mixture; toss until well coated.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into
1-inch pieces and cook in boiling salted water until
tender;
drain.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter or margarine.
Cut chicken into 1 to 2-inch pieces.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: In buttered casserole, layer rice, ham, onion and broccoli. Combine soup, cheese and milk.
Spread over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle fried onion rings over top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: iced curried carrot soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add curry and saute about 3 minutes.
Add carrots, broth and wine.
Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Cool and puree. Just before serving, blend in yogurt and garnish with fresh parsley or cilantro.
Serves 8.

title: ratatouille
directions: In dutch oven cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add the tomatoes and seasoning.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Remove and set aside 2 cups sauce mixture.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order given.
Chill dough 1 hour. Shape into balls of about 1 teaspoon dough.
Flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish (slowly, do not burn).
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with milk.
Pour over oleo, then pour fruit over all.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs and add fruit cocktail.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix in with eggs and fruit cocktail.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Mix brown sugar and chopped nuts; sprinkle over the mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine egg, salt, sugar, vanilla and lemon peel in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Combine milk, rice and raisins.
Stir in egg mix.
Set casserole in pan of hot water filled to 1-inch of top of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir after 30 minutes.

title: smothered ground beef
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. Add salt, pepper, mushroom soup and water. Cover and cook slowly for 20 minutes. Serve on hard toast, corn bread or mash potatoes.

title: danish meat balls(frikadeller)
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Add milk.
Form meat balls with a spoon and fry in margarine until done.

title: pineapple cool whip cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
After pudding thickens, add cream cheese, stirring well until it melts.
Set aside. Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Let cool for 10
minutes after baking.
Spread pudding mixture over cake.
Sprinkle drained crushed pineapple on top of pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple and pudding.
Chill and serve.
Very good!

title: no peek stew
directions: Cut up vegetables and meat; put in a large, greased casserole dish with cover.
Mix tomatoes, soup, tapioca, salt, pepper and garlic.
Mix with meat and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
No peeking!!

title: sweet coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: chicken and wild rice entree
directions: Place chicken breast in 9 x 13 sprayed baking dish.
Top each one with a pat of margarine and a teaspoon of apricot jam.
Place in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cook rice according to directions, using 1/2 cup frozen orange juice as part of water.
Add remaining apricot jam and stir into rice.
Remove chicken breast from baking pan on a plate; pour the rice mixture into the pan.
Place the chicken back on top of the rice and cover with foil.
Return to oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.
(You can spread a little more jam on each piece of chicken.)

title: red hot biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Combine all dry ingredients with a fork, stir in milk and cheese until mixture forms a soft dough. Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Combine butter and remaining garlic powder, brush onto dough tops. Bake 10-12 minutes until golden brown. Makes 12.

title: tomato corn soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Break tomatoes into smaller pieces with a fork.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: sweet-sour onions
directions: Slice onions and arrange in 1-quart baking dish.
Mix ingredients and pour over onions.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: serendipity's punch
directions: Mix jello as directed on box.
Mix all other together, except mint, orange and cherries.
Add mint leaves and orange, sliced very thin.
Chill for at least one hour.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix, bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: italian brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar; mix by hand. Make hole in center of mixture; pour oil in middle.
Beat each egg separately and add to hole.
Mix together.
Add vanilla and nuts. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Peel potatoes and slice whole.
Layer dish or pan across bottom with potatoes.
Peel onions; slice across, making thin slices.
Layer on top of thin sliced potatoes. Peel tomatoes and slice thin; layer on top of onions.
Sprinkle with 1/2 salt.
Sift thin layer flour over tomatoes.
Slice margarine and lay on top of flour.
Repeat entire process.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: bountiful salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss all ingredients.
Cover.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Yield:
6 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Drop by the teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in saucepan; cook on low heat for about 8 minutes.
It will turn brown.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and mix together.
Pour into any size prebuttered pan; let cool.

title: pear butter jam
directions: Boil pears until
soft.
Put
through
food
mill;
add sugar and Karo.
Can put in roaster in oven at low heat or can be put on top
of
stove until right consistency.
When cooked on top of stove, extra
care
must be used to avoid scorching. Nutmeg or cinnamon may be added to taste.
Ladle into jars and seal.

title: short cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut together first five ingredients. Add milk.
Mix.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Bake 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Top with fruit (strawberries) and whipped cream.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Drain fruit together in colander. Keep apricots separate from other fruit. Put in large bowl; add raisins, nuts, 1/2 cup brown sugar and vanilla. Mix. Pour in 9 x 13 baking dish and place apricots over top. Cut toasted bread into 1/2 squares. Mix butter and remaining 1/4 cup brown sugar in shallow dish. Toss
toasted bread squares in butter and brown sugar, coating evenly. Place over entire mixture. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, pimento cheese, and sharp cheddar cheese and mix well.
In a bowl, add onions to warm water and let set until they soften.
Drain onions and squeeze excess water. Add to cheese mixture along with parsley flakes.
Mix thoroughly. Crush pecans.
Make cheese mixture into balls or logs and roll in crushed pecans.
Chill.
This will also freeze well.

title: lotsa chili
directions: Mix together and simmer slowly.
Makes 8 gallons.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain for 2 hours, more or less, the corn, peas and beans. Mince remaining ingredients and pour oil over all vegetables.
Do not stir or toss.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. beat oleo and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs 1 at a time, mixing well after each addition. Add combined dry ingredients alternately with juice, mixing well after each addition. Stir in cranberries, nuts, and grated rind. Pour into greased & floured 9x5 loaf pan. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in centercomes out clean. Cool 10 minutes, remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf. Yummy!
